UPDATE applicants SET major = 'Economics and Applied Math', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/aaryangupta678', why_hillside = 'I became particularly interested in Hillside Ventures after speaking with Burhanudin Ayubali, who has recently joined the organization. Through our conversation, he shared insights into what makes Hillside unique, especially the hands-on exposure to evaluating startups, working with real capital, and learning directly from experienced mentors. Hearing about his experience reinforced my interest in getting involved. Being directly involved in sourcing companies, evaluating opportunities, and presenting investment recommendations is an experience that goes far beyond what can be learned in a classroom.

I’m especially drawn to the collaborative nature of Hillside. Working alongside other motivated UConn students to sharpen presentation skills, build sound investment theses, and engage with founders and alumni is extremely valuable in today’s competitive professional environment. The combination of real capital, mentorship, and peer-driven learning makes Hillside a unique platform to develop practical investing, communication, and networking skills that translate directly to careers in finance and beyond.', contribution = 'As a freshman at UConn majoring in Mathematics and Economics, I bring a strong quantitative mindset to problem solving that I believe would directly contribute to the Genesis Fund. I enjoy applying econometrics, statistical modeling, and coding to real-world questions, and I’ve worked on projects such as Monte Carlo simulations to analyze uncertainty and risk. This analytical approach allows me to evaluate opportunities systematically and support investment decisions with data-driven insights.

In addition to my technical background, my experience as a business intern at a startup has given me valuable perspective on how early-stage companies think about funding, capital efficiency, and long-term sustainability. I’ve seen firsthand how startups allocate limited resources, optimize spending, and make strategic decisions to extend runway. I’ve also been involved in discussions around valuation and determining appropriate funding needs, which would allow me to contribute meaningfully when evaluating potential investments.

Being able to apply my quantitative skills while also drawing on my experience from the operator side would allow me to add value to the Genesis Fund through thoughtful analysis, informed questioning, and well-supported investment recommendations.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Aaryan Gupta';
UPDATE applicants SET major = 'Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/natalieross2028/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures offers a unique opportunity to gain real-world investing experience while leaving a meaningful and lasting impact within UConn’s School of Business. As an accounting student, I am especially interested in applying concepts from my coursework, such as financial statements and reporting, to evaluate the operations and feasibility of real-world companies. The opportunity to support and invest in early-stage startups while actively contributing to their growth is both exciting and highly motivating to me. 
Additionally, I believe Hillside Ventures will help me develop essential analytical, professional, and networking skills that will support my success after graduation. By collaborating with peers, advisors, and industry professionals, I will be able to strengthen my ability to think critically, work within a team, and communicate effectively in a professional setting. I am confident that this experience would not only deepen my understanding of investing, but also prepare me to excel in competitive, high-impact professional environments after graduation.', contribution = 'I hope to contribute to the Genesis Fund by combining my academic foundation in accounting and finance with a strong eagerness to learn and collaborate as a dedicated team member. Through my coursework, I have developed a solid understanding of financial statements and basic valuation concepts, and I am eager to apply this knowledge in a hands-on venture capital environment. 

In addition to my academic experience, my campus involvement has strengthened my understanding of financial management within organizations. I currently work part-time as a Student Administrative Assistant in UConn’s Accounts Payable Office, where I communicate with university vendors to resolve discrepancies in purchase orders and invoice processing. This role has given me valuable insight into financial operations, controls, and vendor relationships, which I believe would translate well to evaluating companies for potential investment. 

I also serve as Treasurer of the Connecticut dormitory residence hall council, where I collaborate with a team to make informed financial decisions related to budgeting and event planning. This experience has strengthened my ability to work responsibly with funds and contribute thoughtfully to group decision-making. 

I am particularly interested in the consumer products sector within the Genesis Fund. Through my role as a HuskyTHON Merchandise Captain, I have gained experience researching consumer trends and contributing to the design and selection of event merchandise. I am excited by the opportunity to translate this experience into evaluating consumer products across a wider range of industries while learning how innovative products scale in competitive markets.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Natalie Ross';
UPDATE applicants SET major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/nick-battaglia-/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures really stands out to me because it offers hands-on experience in venture capital that you just can’t get in a classroom. The chance to source startups, perform due diligence, and see the direct impact of your work is rare at the undergraduate level, and it’s exactly the kind of experience I want at UConn.

Through my coursework here at UConn in finance and analytics, including Investment and Security Analysis, Financial Management, and stock pitches with The Finance Society, I’ve gained a strong foundation in evaluating companies and analyzing financial data. Practical experiences, like managing cash transactions as a bank teller and leading recruitment efforts for my fraternity, have taught me accountability, attention to detail, and working on a team. These are all skills I know will be valuable at Hillside.

What excites me most about Hillside is the combination of prestige, mentorship, and responsibility. Learning from advisors with real industry experience and collaborating with driven peers in a setting where our decisions truly matter is both challenging and motivating. Knowing that the work I contribute could help a startup grow while providing meaningful learning for myself makes Hillside feel like more than just a student organization—it’s a launchpad.

Hillside also connects directly to my career goals in corporate finance. The analytical skills, valuation experience, and exposure to high-stakes decision-making are exactly what I want to develop as I prepare for a career in finance. I see Hillside as a place to contribute, grow, and gain real-world experience that will shape both my professional development and my ability to make a tangible impact.', contribution = 'By applying financial skills, leadership experience, and problem-solving I believe I can make meaningful contributions to both the operations of the Genesis Fund and the success of its portfolio companies. A foundation in financial analysis, valuation, and investment concepts has been built through my coursework such as Investment and Security Analysis, Financial Management, and Managerial Accounting, and reinforced through my projects like a stock pitch for The Finance Society. These experiences required careful evaluation of opportunities, disciplined analysis, and clear communication of recommendations. These skills are central to venture investing.

Leadership roles at UConn have strengthened those qualities. As Head Recruitment Chair for Tau Kappa Epsilon, I managed operations, budgets, and events for a 100+member chapter, which required balancing financial discipline with strategic planning, all while working within a team. Similarly, working as a teller and handling daily financial transactions taught me attention to detail, responsibility, and how to manage real-world financial processes. I feel as though this can directly apply to supporting the fund’s operations and portfolio companies.

Beyond technical and leadership skills, I have worked to build a network across UConn staff, and alumni. This is both a source of guidance and a resource for connecting the fund to valuable insights, expertise, and opportunities. Combined with persistence, and a drive to learn, I am confident this perspective will allow me to consistently contribute to the fund and help portfolio companies in the process. 

All in all, what really stands out about the Genesis Fund is the chance to take on real responsibility, learn from student leaders, and gain experience that actually prepares you for a career in finance. I’m excited about the opportunity to bring my skills and work ethic to help the fund and its portfolio companies, while continuing to grow and learn in the process.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Nicholas Battaglia';
UPDATE applicants SET major = 'BS in Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jake-miller25', why_hillside = 'I’m drawn to Hillside because it matches how I’ve learned to think in the real world: find what’s inefficient, test whether the solution is defensible, and ask the uncomfortable question, “Can this actually scale?” Working in a search-fund environment and spending time around startups taught me to separate compelling stories from durable businesses. I learned to dig into unit economics, customer pain, and operational bottlenecks, then translate those details into a clear investment view.

I want to bring that same execution-first mindset into venture capital. At Hillside, I’m excited to learn alongside people who are intense about turning ideas into outcomes. Being in a room with motivated peers and mentors would push my thinking faster than studying alone, and it would let me contribute in real time through research, diligence, and honest debate.
Hillside also gives me the chance to sharpen how investors evaluate teams, products, and markets. I want to understand what great operators do differently, how distribution gets built, and where growth breaks when fundamentals are weak. I’m especially interested in translating technical concepts into business outcomes: what the product actually changes, why customers adopt it, and how the business scales responsibly. I’m eager to build sourcing discipline, write crisp memos, and support portfolio companies with outreach, recruiting, and go-to-market experiments when needed.

Hillside feels like a place where people challenge assumptions, improve each other’s work, and learn by doing. That’s the environment where I know I’ll grow, and where I can add value from day one.', contribution = 'I can contribute to Hillside through a mix of real-world experience and a genuine drive to learn venture capital the right way. With a background in engineering and economics, I’m used to looking at businesses through a quantitative lens. I focus on fundamentals, how the product works, what the unit economics imply, and where execution risk actually lives. That helps me take a grounded approach to evaluating companies without getting pulled in by branding or polished marketing.

I also bring hands-on operating and finance experience. I’ve built and run a charity initiative from scratch that raised and delivered 120 backpacks for children in need, which taught me how to plan, coordinate logistics, manage stakeholders, and execute under real constraints. More recently, I’ve worked within a search-fund environment doing market research for potential acquisitions in the beauty-spa space. That work forced me to think like an owner: understand the customer, compare competitors, evaluate pricing power, and identify what really drives performance day to day.

These experiences give me insight into how businesses operate beyond spreadsheets. Combined with my quantitative foundation, I can connect numbers to reality, not only understanding the numbers but why they look that way and how a team could improve them. At Hillside, I want to apply that mindset to sourcing, diligence, and investment memos, while learning from people who debate ideas and care about execution.

Venture capital itself excites me. With analytical rigor and real enthusiasm for the process, I know I’ll contribute meaningfully and grow fast at Hillside.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Jake Miller';
UPDATE applicants SET major = 'Statistical Data Science', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/ike-ugwa-3a6424326/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures offers a rare opportunity to engage directly in investing ventures while learning in a rigorous, collaborative environment, that impacts startups with potential. Unlike traditional student organizations Hillside allows students to source, evaluate, and support companies in their early stage with real capital at stake. The organization entrusts members with a generous amount of funds, and rightfully so, as each student is mentored by professors and alumni with industry experience. I am looking towards Hillside specifically for the resources they can provide. With the experience the organization has accumulated, along with the diverse team of students they have built, Hillside has cultivated a culture of excellence as they share wisdom across positions. I wish to be a part of the organization’s success by taking their training and experience joining it with the knowledge I have gained already from online courses and building my person $20,000 investment portfolio. In doing so I hope to better be able to assess risk in different industries and refine my ability to justify decisions with data. Currently, my major is Statistical Data Science, and although it is not a traditional business major the technical skills built into the degree prepare me perfectly for graduate school as I aspire to become a Quant. Hillside’s culture stands out as an environment where I could grow not only technically, but professionally. Through their hands-on projects I can propel my career towards research or internships, increasing my chances of getting accepted into a top master’s program.', contribution = 'My major is Statistical Data Science with a concentration in financial analysis, and I currently serve as a Supplemental Instruction Leader for Statistics 1100, supporting over 200 students in developing a strong understanding of statistical concepts. This role extends beyond earning a high grade in the course; it demonstrates my ability to think critically in terms of data, clearly communicate complex ideas, and apply quantitative reasoning to real-world problems. These skills would be especially valuable to the Genesis Fund when evaluating early-stage companies across its investment verticals, particularly in assessing financial viability, market risk, and growth potential. My background allows me to analyze assumptions behind projections, identify uncertainty in business models, and support data-driven investment decisions that balance impact with long-term value creation.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Ikechukwu Ugwa';
UPDATE applicants SET major = 'Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/-sebastianwroblewski', why_hillside = 'I am drawn to Hillside ventures because it is a unique blend of entrepreneurship and investing. It''s not just evaluating whether an idea is interesting, but whether it can become sustainable and successful. After starting two personal investment portfolios I have become increasingly interested in how startups sustain success. Hillside''s hands-on approach appealed to me as an opportunity not only to learn but also to see the results of this work in action.

Furthermore, I have benefited greatly from mentors, and Hillside would offer a network of knowledgeable upperclassmen who would serve as mentors and friends. As a freshman at UConn who is eager to learn, dig into work, and respond to feedback from mentors, I see Hillside Ventures as a great opportunity to broaden my skill set while building meaningful connections with upperclassmen mentors.

In the long term, I want to develop strong analytical and communication skills within finance, and I see Hillside as a place to grow. Ultimately I aim to take on more responsibility and continue the tradition of mentorship with younger students.', contribution = 'As a freshman, I can contribute to the Genesis Fund in multitudes of ways. Firstly, I will be proactive in deal sourcing and conducting research. I am comfortable reaching out to founders, attending campus and local events, and identifying UConn connected ventures to help expand the fund''s pipeline. 

Specifically, through my background of playing competitive soccer throughout my life and currently participating in Men''s Club Soccer at UConn, I bring a user-level understanding of the sports and wellness sector that is directly relevant to the Genesis Fund''s focus. Being embedded in athletic environments has given me firsthand insight into all ranges of the athletic community and the technology that comes with it. This perspective allows me to help the fund assess sports and wellness startups through the lens of the end user- identifying which products solve real problems, which are likely to scale beyond niche athletic communities, and which may face challenges in adoption or execution.

Also, I also am not afraid of the unglamorous, yet important work- researching markets and turning complex information into a clear and concise statement for the team. I respond well to constructive criticism and try to incorporate it into my work style, which is instrumental to developing as an analyst.

Most importantly, I plan to be reliable and consistent. Whether that means preparing materials, supporting senior analysts, or helping evaluate early-stage ideas, I want to contribute in ways that strengthen the Genesis Fund while continuously learning throughout the process.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Sebastian Wroblewski';
UPDATE applicants SET major = 'Economics and Philosophy', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/-kishan-desai-', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures is what I believe to be a stepping stool into the next step of my career, I believe that the education, mentorship and network will elevate my career to a new level. From a venture that I started last semester to support small businesses within the realm of tech and consulting; to my goals of a career within Finance. I believe that Hillside will offer a unique opportunity to engage in entrepreneurial and educationally stimulating activities and challenges. Hillside Ventures will give me the chance to build heavily on my presentations skills, a skill that I know will play a crucial role in future opportunities. Additionally, the focus on financial analysis will help set me ahead within my career progression as I engage with financial models and explore different analytical roles. A big part of Hillside that I know will be of great value is the mentorship that is found within the organization, with the mentors developing students into great talent. Alongside the mentorship is the network I am hoping to join, from Managing Directors to C-Suite executives; I know that this incredible roster of professionals will elevate my career. Possibly one of the most pivotal aspects in my application to Hillside Ventures is the education within regards to understanding proper venture decisions, developing the skills of research and organization in order to create real value. I believe that a role within this organization will give me the opportunity not only to become a more impressive student, but develop into a better overall professional.', contribution = 'The biggest contribution I believe I can give to the Genesis fund is my prior experiences mixed with a desire to learn and develop. Over the past six months, I have been developing my own venture, which I can now proudly say is not only a concept, but a passion project that is earning recurring positive revenue. This experience has rebuilt my mindset of what it takes to be successful and what it means to be a student, having become one of my greatest learning endeavors. On top of the research and client facing position that I have accomplished with my business, I will also have completed an internship within investor relations and research advisory this upcoming summer. This experience is something that I believe will help me strongly contribute to the Genesis Fund, as it gives me in depth insight on many of the topics that the fund values. Furthermore, my involvement in various organizations and courseload has furthered my skills within analysis and time management. Additionally, I offer my previous experiences, including that of being a Business Strategist intern last summer within a pharmaceutical group run by my family, a summer that involved in depth analysis, competitor research, and strategy development. Having grown up in an entrepreneurial family, I can attest to the devotion and hard work that it takes to develop something great. However, I know that my greatest contribution to the fund will be my hunger for knowledge and development; as someone who knows that every opportunity comes with commitment, I am ready to open up to new knowledge and challenges. I have always been someone who has pushed to be the greatest in whatever I pursue, from being the captain of my wrestling team in high school, to executive boards in college organizations; I understand the importance of balance, commitment and communication.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Kishan Desai';
UPDATE applicants SET major = 'Finance and Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/kunal-ramchandani-b71bb7336', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures really stands out to me because it offers a rare opportunity to learn and understand venture capitals by engaging in the evaluation and support of the early-stage startups, instead of only reading and studying about them. The Genesis Fund''s attention to the student-led investing and the close relations to the founders is something that grabs my attention right away. I know from experience this creates for an environment where the knowledge is gained through fast paced hands-on work. 

I am particularly drawn to Hillside''s focus on developing technologies and innovated ecosystems. As someone who has a strong passion for financial technology and wealth management, I appreciate how this program motivates students to truly understand the evolving markets and risk factors that are actively changing the future of Finance. This vertical-based structure acknowledges the specialization in different areas, but also allows for collaboration which is super important. This structure mirrors the successful venture teams that operate in the real world and this is something I love. 

For me, Hillside Ventures isn''t just an opportunity to invest. It is a chance to learn about strong mentorship, founder engagement, and a strong point on pensive decision-making. These three things are exactly the type of points that I want to experience to grow professionally. I am driven and committed to putting my analytical mindset to use and sharing my interest in FinTech with peers and mentors who are as eager as me. To summarize the question Why Hillside Ventures in one sentence - here is my answer. Hillside Ventures represents the perfect cross between education, innovation, and real-world experience that I am actively seeking at this stage of my career.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by introducing myself with a disciplined, thesis-driven approach to assessing these fintech startups that go with Hillside''s Financial Innovation Map. I am particularly interested in doing research on how companies operate within the broader financial ecosystem, from data-driven tools to  payments and basic infrastructure. The idea that their solutions can significantly change efficiency, friction, and even broaden access to financial services is very interesting to me. 

Within the Financial Technology vertical, I would contribute by applying Hillside''s foundation to assess these startups beyond the surface-level. I would bring knowledge and help out in researching where a companies books are financially, how tenable its solution is, and whether its theory is made from innovation or optimization. I would love the opportunity to engage with peers in market mapping, shared analysis, and a structured effort to find financially positive long-term outcomes. 

I work best in group settings because I am always active and thoughtful. As President of Wealth Management Society and Vice President of Finance for my fraternity, I know how to ask the right questions, support my decisions, and also engage in constructive feedback. I know for a team to work well, there needs to be accountability, collaboration, and most importantly communication. These are extremely important for a student-led investment fund to make real-world decisions.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Kunal Ramchandani';
