UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Analytics and Information Management', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/caleb-awuah-970a95375/', why_hillside = 'Even before college, I was often the person explaining how things worked. I remember helping my aunt set up her first online banking account, walking her through apps, fees, so she could efficiently manage her money. Around the same time, I watched a close family friend develop and launch his own brilliant small tech enabled business that was never able to take off due to lack of funding and support to properly execute it. Seeing that sparked my interest in the moments where the right move or resource can determine whether a venture struggles or scales. Hillside stands out to me because it evaluates startups through specific industry verticals. I’m intrigued by how ventures are assessed from multiple viewpoints including the startup’s financials, how well they solve a meaningful problem and achieve product market fit within areas like financial innovation and consumer products.', contribution = 'I would contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a perspective that is grounded in clarity and practicality. I would naturally approach new ventures by asking whether an idea is both promising and practical in the real world. In group settings, I tend to be the person who asks questions and seeks clarity. I''ve learned that many ideas sound great at first glance, but begin to fall apart when you examine how users would actually interact with them. I’m especially interested in financial innovation because I’ve seen how confusing and inaccessible financial tools can be for people. That perspective allows me to evaluate fintech startups not only by their numbers, but by how clearly they solve an issue, and how easily they can be adopted by the people they are meant to serve. At Genesis, I would contribute by looking beyond what is impressive in theory and focus on what is viable in practice.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Caleb Awuah';
