UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Analytics and Information Management', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/ahmed-osman-67b93736b/', why_hillside = 'I am applying to Hillside Ventures because it truly represents experiential learning at Uconn, bridging the gap between my academic focus and real-world capital allocation. While my course work provides the technical foundation, Hillside really offers the unique opportunity to apply those skills to a portfolio with real financial stakes. I want to transition from academic exercises to apply my technical skills to the due diligence process for early-stage startups. What draws me to Hillside is its commitment to applied learning and its reputation for developing analysts who are both technically proficient and strategically minded. I am eager to learn from the fund''s mentors and peers to build the foundation for evaluating early-stage innovation, while also gaining a clear understanding of the venture capital field. Overall joining Hillside provides the hands-on experience and professional accountability I need to grow.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by applying my technical background to the due diligence process. I will use these skills to analyze consumer behavior and market trends. My experience as Director of Events for the First-Generation Business Society has prepared me to manage professional responsibilities and collaborate with a team. Previously, as the prior President of the Technology Student Association in my high school, I analyzed budget data to fund competitions for my peers. I will bring this same analytical rigor to Hillside when start ups. I will put in 101% in Hillside and am committed to sourcing diverse founders and identifying companies with strong data-driven foundations.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Ahmed Osman';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.75, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/vincent-ly-16767b304', why_hillside = 'I heard about Hillside Ventures through mutual connections and from a classmate (current analyst), who gave an in class presentation about Hillside. Hillside Ventures seems like a great opportunity to learn and gain hands on experience with real world investment practices. The exposure to working directly with founders and industry experts, while learning how to invest, is a unique experience that would definitely add value to my learning. After attending the second info session, I was intrigued on how the process worked, through due diligence, to sourcing companies, holding founder calls, and writing memos to the board before getting it approved at the end. I also learned the basics, but in my opinion useful information when researching companies, such as seeds (preseed, seed, series A), exits, MRR, and more. Overall, I definitely believe that Hillside Ventures can add value to my learning, open doors to new opportunities, and build skills in presenting in a concise and visually appealing manner.', contribution = 'To be frank, I think I do best at breaking things down so people can understand them in a simple and clear way. I believe I would contribute not only through research but also by building genuine connections to understand the needs of founders and what they''re looking for. This makes it more easier for decision making, stronger collaboration between the analyst and founder, and understanding the best ways to support the founders. I also have experience with reaching out and networking closely with alumni from UConn and successful entrepreneurs who are able to provide insight on their success, which can be translated over to predicting whether the other startups are worth it/ "kill it"', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Vincent Ly';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.77, major = 'Finance / German Studies Major', expected_graduation = 'Other', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/luka-vidacak/', why_hillside = 'I chose Hillside Ventures due to my passion for sustainability, and I my goal to pursue the development and creation of businesses as a long-term career. I want to gain practical experience in research and investing in early funding for budding companies that could have a positive impact on the world, through ESG.  Hillside venture and its sustainability vertical align with my long-term goals of creating long term positive change through funding of new technologies and its applications.', contribution = 'Being in the EuroBiz program, with a strong interest in sustainability, I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a combination of analytical skill, global perspective, and sector_specific insight. My finance background allows me to evaluate unit economics, financial projections, and valuation logic, while my sustainability focus helps me assess long_term viability, ESG alignment, and potential regulatory risks. I’m also able to draw on my German studies to provide perspective on European markets, especially in areas like cleantech and environmental regulation where the EU is a global leader. Beyond diligence, I can contribute by supporting founder outreach and helping craft clear, thoughtful investment memos.  I hope to strengthen Genesis’s ability to identify resilient, impactful, and sustainable companies while growing as an VC investor myself.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Luka Vidacak';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.6, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/kaylaphuongle/', why_hillside = 'I recently discovered that I’m interested in venture capital and would like to explore my curiosity by being about of Hillside Ventures. I’ve always heard great things about the student fund and would love the opportunity to be a part of it.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing in strong teamwork and analytical skills. I believe that strong communication within a team is extremely crucial, especially when it comes to investing. I’m very eager to learn and apply analytical skills.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Kayla Le';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.4, major = 'Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/omar-omar-5927212b2/', why_hillside = 'I''m really interested in Hillside Ventures because it gives me an opportunity to explore a student-run fund here at UConn for the first time, giving undergrads like me a chance to experience the real side of venture capital. Actually taking the time to do the due diligence, source real companies, and learn how to evaluate early startups. As an Economics major with a strong interest in investing, I''ve always been fascinated by how capital flows into creative ideas, but I''ve never had the opportunity to get involved in the VC side yet. The Genesis Fund specifically excites me because of its focus on areas like Consumer Products and Fin-Tech, sectors that really relate to my own passions for building efficient businesses (like the family limo company I co-founded and helped run). 

Being a part of Hillside Ventures in a student-led team would allow me to further advance my current skills. Such as my background in website design and development (helping launch and shape a limo transportation company website for better bookings and user experience), basic Python and SQL for data analysis, and particularly my OSINT (Open Source Intelligence) knowledge for researching markets or founders. Additionally, the mentorship from the industry professionals and the wide network of alumni would be huge for me as a first-gen student. I''ve already witnessed the value of mentorship through my bi-weekly sessions in UConn''s first-gen business society as well as through UConn''s Muslim Student Association where they have personalized business mentorships every week. Through these mentorships I''ve been constantly working on my career goals from resume building to knowledge around finance, tech, and data analysis. To me, Hillside feels like the ideal next step to bridge my experience in operational management, investing knowledge, and research capabilities to evaluate upcoming startups to truly understand what value they hold and what risks come along with that.', contribution = 'I believe I can bring a mix of beneficial entreprenuerial experience, technical skills, and a strong disciplined work ethic to the Genesis Fund team. Having co-founded and served as an Operations Manager for Global Limousine (a limo transportation company) since 2022, I''ve handled real world business operations, managing high volume customer calls, coordinating multiple driver routes throughout the tri-state area (CT, NY, Mass), processing payments securely, and collaborated on website design to improve user experience and easily accessible quotes. I''ve gained a deeper insight into a real active customer based business and know what action to take whether it be branding, customer profiles, or optimizing a website. These skills would be greatly beneficial when it comes to dechipering the best startups in all verticals but especially Fin-Tech.

On the technical side, I have core knowledge in Python and SQL for data handling, Excel for simple analysis and visual guides, and website development, all of which could support tasks like market researching, collecting and evaluating data on potential investments, or even breaking down what makes a startups digital presence or product work or not work. My current part time roles at SAS Retail Services, where I execute detailed merchandising plans and collaborate with teams under specific deadlines, aswell as Amazon DSP, where I organize logistics and execute high volume deliveries, all contribute to my ability to work efficiently in fast paced environments where attention to detail are held to a high standard. These responsibilities often go overnight or in challenging conditions which translate well to the demanding nature of VC where I have to deal with sourcing the best of the best with extreme attentiveness.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Omar Omar';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.5, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/thomson-tran/', why_hillside = 'I am motivated for the opportunities and doors that could open if I were able to receive an opportunity of being part of Hillside Ventures. As a Finance major, I am always looking for more opportunities and projects that can further develop a stronger foundation in finance, collaboration, and analytic skills. Not only does this program offer an intensive and collaborative experience, I hope to gain from this experience is allowing myself to gain meaningful exposure to professionals and peers who are passionate and determined like myself. I am looking for an opportunity to increase my connections and network as these interactions can contribute to bettering my chances towards my career and having peers alongside me. Additionally, I plan on gaining more insight in venture capital and private equity as I know that there are a lot of opportunities and a great future that lies ahead in terms of this industry. This opportunity represents an important step in bridging my academic foundation with my professional aspirations.', contribution = 'I would bring my curiosity, my persistence, and my ability to get things done to the Genesis Fund. Venture capital is a new world for me, but I''m eager to learn and put the effort into developing a solid foundation of knowledge in this industry. I''m someone who thrives in a dynamic environment that''s constantly changing. When faced with new challenges, I''m able to adapt quickly. My persistence allows me to finish tasks well, whether that means doing extensive research or helping the team stay organized. I''m someone who shows up every day and gets the job done. But most importantly, I''m a learner. I''m someone who asks great questions, seeks feedback, and challenges myself to understand the why of the decisions we make. I believe that these traits, combined with my ability to get things done and my willingness to be a team player, would allow me to make an impact at the Genesis Fund from the very start.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Thomson Tran';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.5, major = 'Finance/Statistics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://linkedin.com/in/matteofesta', why_hillside = 'I’m interested in Hillside because it’s real exposure to early-stage investing, not just talking about startups, or hypothetical questions like in class. I like evaluating companies and thinking through whether something will actually work long term. In underwriting, I looked at management teams, financials, and overall risk before decisions were made. A lot of that comes down to making calls with incomplete information, which is similar to venture.

I want to be in a group where decisions are based on analysis and discussion, not surface-level excitement. Hillside seems like a place where I can apply my finance and statistics background in a practical way while learning how early-stage investment decisions are made.', contribution = 'I can bring strong financial analysis and a risk-focused mindset. At ATRI Insurance Services, I analyzed balance sheets, income statements, and cash flow statements to evaluate company risk and understand how leadership decisions and capital structure impact long-term stability. I also presented my findings in front of the underwriting team, which helped me get comfortable explaining my thinking and answering questions in a group setting.

I’ll be returning to ATRI again this summer, so I’ll continue building experience evaluating companies before starting at Hillside in the fall. That exposure to real decision-making will strengthen how I think about risk and financial discipline in early-stage businesses.

I also helped build my fraternity chapter from the ground up, which gives me perspective on what it’s like to structure something early and work through uncertainty. I’m comfortable speaking up, breaking down numbers, and contributing to team discussions.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Matteo Festa';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.89, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/colin-mcgann-d54890/', why_hillside = 'I am drawn to Hillside Ventures because the oppurtunity to work alongside so many students who have the same passion for investing is something that truly excites me. Beyond that collaboration, I am super interested in Hillside and the oppurtunity to contribute to early-stage startups and gain experience in investment research, due diligence, and sourcing deals. Most importantly, the opportunity to collaborate with peers and professionals that directly support my career goals in finance and investing is an oppurtunity that I wouldn''t take for granted.', contribution = 'I would contribute a mix of analytical thinking and curiosity. I genuinely care about valuation, investing, and understanding data driven decisions. Beyond analytical thinking, I bring a strong collaborative mindset and love working in team environments. I believe that any question is a good question and this is something I would bring every single day to Hillside. To conclude if selected for Hillside, I would bring a motivated mindset that would not only be dedicated to the work at hand but a curious mindset, pushing others to learn.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Colin McGann';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.94, major = 'Finance/Minor in Real Estate', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/-clive-leung/', why_hillside = 'I am drawn to Hillside Ventures because the learning environment helps me develop as a finance student and as a person outside of the classroom.  Being unfamiliar with the venture capital industry, Hillside allows me to work alongside like-minded peers to help gain this exposure.  I would be able to learn from the perspectives and ideas of my peers while being challenged to grow at a higher level, strengthening my ability to work in a team setting.  This strong learning environment would allow me to make the most of the opportunity provided, whether through learning about new topics or skills or creating meaningful connections that can help boost my professional growth.  Being a finance major, I learn a lot of concepts and topics in the classroom.  Hillside provides the opportunity to connect these topics to real experience. It immerses me in the venture capital process from start to finish. This unique experience would develop my understanding of finance into something tangible, which can be applied to any professional environment. 

Additionally, Hillside would provide me a strong foundation for any career path in finance, like wealth management or investment banking. From company analysis to due diligence, the process allows me to manage real capital that can influence investment decisions, which is something that excites me.  Lastly, I am excited about the vertical structure of the fund.  I believe that with the vertical structure, I can extend my interests in certain topics like consumer products into the finance world through Hillside.  It provides the ability to connect with founders and companies in the industry, which I am strongly interested in as it allows me to learn more. Overall, Hillside provides a holistic learning experience for me where I would be able to gain hands-on experience and develop other skills like communication.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by offering a diverse perspective that comes from an analytical mindset, along with a collaborative outlook driven by my willingness to learn.  I enjoy learning from diverse perspectives in a group environment, as these ideas can come together and form an efficient way and outlook on certain problems. In a team environment, I provide a diverse and different perspective that not only can contribute to the outcome of our actions but can also allow me to teach and learn something new.  By fostering and valuing this open team environment, this would allow more efficient work processes with more collaboration and open communication, where every perspective can be valued.  This also allows a fresh learning experience for me as I can learn from others and use their opinions and perspectives to help influence my judgment positively when performing tasks such as company research or due diligence.  My team-oriented approach to issues, open mind, and collaborative outlook can contribute positively to a strong learning/working environment.

I can also contribute an analytical mindset with strong attention to detail.  My experiences here at UConn have my experiences have allowed me to develop an analytical mindset. From my coursework and recruiting training, I have gained confidence in financial modeling and risk analysis.  I look to be able to contribute and expand on my financial modelling skills to where it can make processes more efficient when closing out deals. This is why the financial Modelling role in Hillside attracts me, as I can contribute my modelling and analytical skills and learning from my peers as well.  In addition to my skills, I also offer enthusiasm and dependability. To contribute to the success of the whole fund, it is a team effort. Whether it is cold emailing, industry research, or preparing pitch materials, I am ready to ensure that all goals and efforts are met.  Thus, I can contribute a positive, open, and ready-to-work or learn mindset to Hillside.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Clive Leung';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.79, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/tristan-gorman', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures is a great opportunity to take what I have learned from my involvement in Finance Society and Investment Banking Society, and apply it and get real world experience working with startup companies and helping them grow, while also growing my knowledge of finance and building skills such as problem-solving, creative and critical thinking, and professionalism. I have been able to meet and interact with multiple people involved in Hillside through different outlets, and it is clear to me that it is a group of driven students looking to innovate and make a difference.', contribution = 'I would be a great fit for the Genesis Fund because based on looking into the four verticals, it appears that the Fund is focused on creating a bigger and brighter future, and I am just as motivated to do the same. Being apart of something that is making a difference in the everyday world, specifically at the grassroots level, is a great opportunity to showcase my innovative abilities I am confident that when surrounded by a team of like-minded individuals, I can take on any challenge or task head-on, and produce results that will meet the goals of both the team and the startup. If selected to be an analyst, I would bring essential qualities such as effective communication skills, accountability, and intellectual curiosity that would improve the overall environment of the team. Working in a team drives me to excel in order to meet and even exceed expectations, and I have successfully done so in past experiences that have prepared me for experiences like the Genesis Fund.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Tristan Gorman';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.2, major = 'Finance with a minor in math', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/mohammed-nur-b75b29313/', why_hillside = 'I want to join Hillside Ventures because it’s one of the few places at UConn where you actually get to work on real startups. I’ve done fundraising and projects where I had to dig into numbers and figure out what works, and I want to take those skills and see how they apply to evaluating early-stage companies.', contribution = 'I can contribute by bringing the skills I’ve built in my finance and math classes like analyzing financial statements, working through complex problems in linear algebra and in Calculus 3. On top of that, my fundraising experience taught me how to dig into data that I already have and make clear recommendations. I’d use all of that to research startups, break down their financials, and help the Fund make smarter investment decisions.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Mohammed Nur';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance major, Analytics minor', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/chloe-morales28', why_hillside = 'From the conversations I have had with current Hillside analysts, it is evident that Hillside Ventures is a highly effective, hands-on VC Fund that equips students with direct experience in assessing investment opportunities, conducting due diligence, and directly engaging with early-stage company leaders. Although all four verticals in the Genesis Fund are compelling, I am particularly drawn to Financial Innovation. This sector fascinates me amid growing uncertainty in AI and tech startups gaining massive valuations extremely quickly despite lacking products and relying solely on research teams with no concrete findings or revenue yet. I am hopeful and eager to dive into Hillside’s due diligence processes and conduct thorough analysis to identify startups with true growth potential in such a unique industry environment. Additionally, through my past experiences I have discovered that I thrive in collaborative environments and Hillside would allow me the chance to connect and work with like-minded peers who share my passion for seeking out and evaluating worthwhile investment opportunities.', contribution = 'I am a dependable person and always give whatever task I’m handed my full effort, consistently trying my hardest to deliver high quality results. As I stated in my previous response, I also thrive in team-oriented environments. During my freshman year, I worked as a research assistant for an Economics professor, and I quickly adapted to my team’s dynamics and learned that everyone brings their own unique skillsets to produce quality results. I focused on identifying and leveraging those strengths, whether it was through targeted questions, or dividing research tasks effectively and intentionally, which consistently led to quality, insightful findings under tight deadlines. I would bring this same proactive approach to Hillside. By fostering collaboration within my vertical group, I would help produce high quality pitches that accurately reflect the promising startups that we source.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Chloe Morales';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.6, major = 'Major: Finance, Minor: Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/adithya-nataraj1', why_hillside = 'So far in my college career I have mostly lived in the world of theory. Most of my learning and education would lead me to a certain point which would be a career in the real world where my education and experience meets quantifiable application. That is exactly why I believe that Hillside offers the space where my analysis and conversations with founders can turn into real deals. After some coffee chats with members, my interest in Hillside grew even further than I thought. I had curated a list of specific questions that would help me understand the process of the deal flows. In some other cases, the answers tend to be very generic when asked a specific question which shows that person isn''t well versed in their work. However, each member in Hillside was able to talk me through their thought process and what to look for when studying a pitch deck and data room. They provided very interesting insights on how to evaluate the numbers, strategy and people of the company. I had asked a question about what the consistent theme was about the winner companies and the steps it takes to get a deal. The answers I received revealed the thoughtfulness and discipline that define the Hillside way of investing. Another fun reason is I watch Shark Tank every day and love analyzing the numbers, strategy, and people behind each pitch. Hillside gives me the chance to go beyond the show and experience that process firsthand. Lastly, I would like to mention the culture of Hillside. I felt the drive, curiosity and discipline of each person in Hillside which felt like a strong brother and sisterhood. Being around that kind of environment confirmed that this is where I want to learn and contribute. Hillside felt like a microcosm of the investing world and I am excited to be a part of it.', contribution = 'I will contribute to the Genesis Fund by fully committing to the team and the work required to make smart insights. I believe a collaborative environment is key and would actively share insights, ask thoughtful questions, and support team members in evaluating companies. I enjoy understanding the vision of founders, which can help me contribute by seeing the big picture of a company’s potential and find risks that don’t come from numbers alone. With my finance major and accounting minor I think a lot of the work would overlap when reading data and statements and also the networking aspect with founders. This would allow my team and I to better understand a company’s financial health and growth potential, making the information more accurate and reliable. These are some reasons I am dedicated to the process and believe that what you put in is what you get out.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Adithya Nataraj';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.4, major = 'Economics, Anayltics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/kuba-gaska-851127332', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures gives me the opportunity to continue to grow my analytical and strategic thinking skills. I want to challenge myself beyond the classroom and apply economic reasoning and data analysis in real life investment decisions. Additionally, I am looking to be apart of something bigger than myself and meet more students who are driven to work together towards a common goal. Hillside Ventures would give me the opportunity to grow alongside my peers, contribute to a strong organization, and help me develop leadership skills that will shape my future career.', contribution = 'With my past experience in the construction industry, i''m interested in contributing in the genesis fund through the sustainability category. My exposure to large projects and design has shown me first hand how energy efficiency and long time environmental impacts all interact with real world decision making. I am interested in evaluating companies that focus on building materials, energy efficient technologies, sustainable supply chains and ESG driven innovation because these solutions are becoming essential, for both the economy and society.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Kuba';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.57, major = 'Finance/Analytics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrew-vaill-519820294/', why_hillside = 'Hillside offers an incredible opportunity to gain real-world experience in the venture capital industry with strong mentorship from experienced professionals. As someone who would like to pursue this career path, I aim to enhance my career readiness and this program will further my knowledge on venture funds.', contribution = 'As a motivated, problem-solver with strong communication skills, I can contribute especially in a team environment as I feel I work best in a group. I enjoy being collaborative and working with others to find the best solution possible to a given problem.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Andrew Vaill';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.59, major = 'Economics/Women&Gender Studies', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/israela-anane', why_hillside = 'I am interested in Hillside Ventures because it offers hands-on exposure to how early-stage companies are evaluated, supported, and scaled, which directly aligns with my interest in finance and business strategy. What draws me to Hillside most is the opportunity to learn by doing. Rather than just studying concepts in class, Hillside allows students to actively analyze companies, ask the right questions, and understand how real investment decisions are made. I’m especially excited about Hillside’s collaborative, student-driven environment. As someone currently in the process of building a new student organization focused on career development and leadership, I’m especially drawn to Hillside’s emphasis on early-stage thinking, initiative, and learning through real responsibility. As a founder and president of a student organization, I value spaces where initiative, teamwork, and accountability matter. Hillside mirrors that same culture, where students are trusted with real responsibility while being mentored by experienced professionals. Hillside represents the intersection of finance, leadership, and impact for me. It’s a space where I can build strong analytical and professional skills early on, while learning how thoughtful investment decisions can support innovative founders and growing businesses.', contribution = 'I know I can contribute to the Genesis Fund through my strong work ethic, curiosity, and a willingness to take ownership of my responsibilities. I have a lot of experience working in fast-paced, team-based environments where attention to detail, communication, and follow-through matter. Through my background in talent acquisition and leadership, I’m comfortable asking thoughtful questions, organizing information, and supporting decision-making processes. As an economics student interested in finance, I’m eager to learn how to evaluate companies, understand business models, and contribute to due diligence efforts. I approach new challenges with an open mindset and strong discipline, and I’m not afraid to put in the time to build skills quickly. I also value collaboration and accountability, and I would contribute positively to the Genesis Fund’s team culture by being reliable, engaged, and prepared.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Israela Anane';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.51, major = 'Finance/Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/amir-alston/', why_hillside = 'What attracts me to Hillside Ventures is the blending between community impact and venture capital. It provides opportunities for students, like myself, to assist student founders while also providing an interactive environment for to learn about sourcing, screening, and making investment decisions while assisting actual start ups at UConn. My interest in finance and entrepreneurship is in line with that mission. 

Through my own experience in investing and market evaluation, I have the ability to think critically about risk, growth potential, and long-term value. I want to use those abilities in a collaborative environment where we look beyond the numbers to comprehend the founders'' goals, sustainability, and product-market fit. Given that it prioritizes learning, mentoring, and careful investing over merely allocating capital, Hillside''s collaborative culture is especially intriguing.

Hillside''s contribution to strengthening the campus ecosystem for business also inspires me. Long-lasting social and economic effects can be produced by assisting diverse founders and early-stage concepts. I would be able to advance professionally and assist other students in transforming their ideas into meaningful businesses by joining Hillside.', contribution = 'Through strong and credible research, financial analysis, and active sourcing, I can support the Genesis Fund. With my experience in stock trading and studies in finance and statistics, I’m comfortable evaluating market trends, reviewing financial projections, and identifying key risks and opportunities. I enjoy digging into industries, comparing competitors, and presenting clear investment memos that help teams make informed decisions.

I also bring my interest in new developments in technology. I am willing to pick up technical concepts efficiently and turn them into business insights, such as evaluating product effectiveness, market size, and growth strategy, because when searching about the Genesis Fund I found that many Genesis Fund startups will be early-stage and STEM-focused.

Overall, I believe that I can help by fusing dependable teamwork with active outreach. In addition to meeting deadlines, communicating effectively, and providing my peers with insightful analysis, I''m driven to establish connections with founders in the fields of computer science, engineering, and business in order to strengthen our pipeline and establish relationships early on. I want to use these efforts to assist the Genesis Fund in identifying and supporting businesses that have solid foundations and significant potential.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Amir Alston';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.79, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/dev-gorasiya/', why_hillside = 'I am drawn to Hillside Ventures because it offers the rare opportunity to learn venture capital through real, hands-on experience rather than purely theoretical coursework. As someone deeply interested in business and investing, I want to understand how strong startups are identified, evaluated, and supported at the early stage. Hillside’s student-led diligence process combined with mentorship from experienced faculty creates the kind of high-impact learning environment I am actively seeking.

What particularly excites me is Hillside’s focus on early-stage investing, where thoughtful analysis and disciplined decision-making can meaningfully influence a company’s trajectory. I am especially interested in the Consumer Products vertical because I naturally pay attention to how everyday products differentiate themselves through branding, pricing, and customer value. I enjoy thinking critically about what drives consumer adoption and long-term scalability.

Beyond skill-building, I see Hillside as a platform to develop strong investment judgment, collaborate with driven peers, and gain exposure to the venture ecosystem. Given my long-term interest in pursuing a career in finance or investing, I believe Hillside Ventures is the ideal place to build both the technical and strategic foundation necessary to succeed.', contribution = 'I would contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing strong analytical curiosity, disciplined research habits, and a genuine willingness to do the detailed work required in early-stage diligence. I am comfortable digging into data, asking thoughtful questions, and breaking down complex business models to understand where real value is being created.

Through my experience with VITA and leadership involvement at UConn, I have developed attention to detail, accountability, and the ability to work effectively in team-based environments. I plan to apply these strengths when sourcing deals, conducting market research, and evaluating startups within the Consumer Products space. I bring a consumer-first mindset. I naturally observe market trends, customer behavior, and product positioning in everyday life, which I believe is valuable when assessing early-stage consumer companies. I would aim to contribute thoughtful insights during diligence discussions and support the team in identifying startups that show strong product-market fit and scalable growth potential.

Most importantly, I bring a strong learning mindset. I am eager to absorb feedback, continuously improve my investment thinking, and contribute wherever the team needs support. My goal is to add value through consistent, high-quality work while growing into a thoughtful and reliable member of the Genesis Fund team.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Dev Gorasiya';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Economics Major, intended Political Science Minor', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/benjamin-anderson333', why_hillside = 'I want to join Hillside Ventures because the opportunity to source high-potential startups while working with a driven team of UConn students genuinely excites me. I’m drawn to the hands-on experience of analyzing startups and contributing to a real investment process under strong professional mentorship. I’m motivated to evaluate innovative companies, think critically about their growth and market, and add meaningful value to the fund. Researching companies that are innovating and adapting to current market trends inspires me, as analyzing businesses and markets is something I’m truly passionate about.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund through my experience in high-pressure, detail-oriented environments and my deep interest in the Consumer Products vertical, specifically food & beverage. Having worked in the food industry alongside accomplished chefs, I have developed firsthand knowledge of nutrition, taste, operational efficiency, and evolving consumer preferences. This background allows me to think critically about products, branding, and scalability in this vertical. Paired with my interest in analyzing businesses and market trends as an Economics major, I stay actively informed on current events and consumer trends, which I believe would be an important asset when evaluating opportunities within the fund.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Benjamin Anderson';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.6, major = 'ACES', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/brenden-boyer', why_hillside = 'I want to join Hillside Ventures because it offers a hands on opportunity to learn how early stage investing works while also being a part of a student driven community. Being involved would allow me to develop skills in financial analysis and market research in a team environment and learn from others around me.', contribution = 'I could contribute to the Genesis Fund by being an engaged and reliable team member who brings strong curiosity to every stage of the investment process. I’m comfortable working in team environments and taking initiative whether it’s for researching markets or evaluating start up pitches. I’m also willing to take on all kinds of work beyond those two such as organizing data and assisting with presentations. Most importantly, I bring a genuine interest in learning and improving myself and am committed to consistently contributing to the funds success.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Brenden Boyer';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/zachharrison', why_hillside = 'I am interested in Hillside Ventures because I seek to not only acquire knowledge throughout my undergraduate career, but also apply these skills to real-world contexts. As a freshman finance major, one of the opportunities I am most excited about is working with live investments, which is a reason I am particularly interested in Hillside. From direct communication with founders who pioneer innovative technologies to collaborating with peers to close these deals, there are many opportunities for meaningful and purposeful growth at Hillside. Moreover, the responsibility of performing rigorous due diligence on startups, where real money has the potential to be invested, aligns with my post-graduate aspirations, where I plan on pursuing a career in finance. I strongly believe in the power of startups and am passionate about helping small companies grow and continue on a path toward profitability. Learning how to evaluate early-stage businesses is meaningful to me because it combines analytical rigor with real impact. My interest in venture capital, asset management, wealth management, and technology especially aligns perfectly with the work being done at Hillside, and I am confident that the experience and knowledge gained from those within it would prove valuable. My own past experiences interning at Young American Capital and in UConn’s finance society, where I participated in the stock pitch competition, have lit a fire under me to seek out similar opportunities. Next semester, I know that there is no better avenue to pursue than Hillside Ventures.', contribution = 'From my past experiences and expertise, I am confident that I would be a strong asset to the Genesis Fund. I am currently pursuing educational opportunities to further strengthen my financial background through the Wall Street Prep program, to which I was accepted through a selective initiative within the School of Business. This training has allowed me to develop a working understanding of company valuation methodologies, gain foundational exposure to portfolio construction and analysis, and practical skills in Microsoft Office. Through this experience, I have strengthened my ability to analyze financial information, interpret data, and approach problems in a structured and detail-oriented manner. I am confident that these skills will enable me to contribute effectively to investment research, collaborative projects, and team-based decision-making across the fund. In addition to my technical preparation, I bring a motivated and self-driven work ethic, along with an outgoing and collaborative personality. I am comfortable working both independently and in team environments, and I consistently seek opportunities to take initiative and support group objectives. I believe these qualities position me well to add value as a dependable team member and to become a leader within Hillside. I also aim to make a lasting impact by raising awareness of the fund beyond the UConn community. Making this opportunity more visible to prospective applicants would cause more talented students to matriculate at UConn. In Hillside, I am eager to continue learning, refine my skills, and contribute meaningfully to the fund’s success and sustainability.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Zachary Harrison';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.91, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/rahulperumal123', why_hillside = 'I’m interested in Hillside Ventures because I want real, hands-on experience with how startups grow and how investment decisions actually get made. As a Finance major at UConn, I’ve spent a lot of time learning the technical side in class, but I’m really motivated to see how that connects to evaluating founders, markets, and ideas in the real world. Through my leadership roles and case competitions, I’ve learned that I enjoy fast-paced, team-driven environments where you have to think critically and make decisions with incomplete information, which is very similar to venture investing. Hillside also stands out to me because it focuses on learning by doing and gives students the chance to work closely with entrepreneurs, which is exactly the kind of experience I’m looking for as I explore careers in finance and potentially venture capital. Overall, I see this as a place where I can both contribute and grow a lot.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by supporting its goal of identifying strong early-stage companies while helping maintain a collaborative, student-led investment process. As a Finance major at UConn, I’ve developed analytical skills through coursework and experiences like placing second in the Mannheim Aldi Competition, where I evaluated business strategy and financial performance.

In my leadership role as Director of Fundraising for the Sports Business Association, I’ve managed projects, worked closely with teams, and helped raise over $5,000, which strengthened my ability to execute, communicate, and stay organized—skills that translate directly to research, diligence, and fund operations. I’m naturally curious about how businesses grow and willing to put in the time to analyze opportunities and support the team in making thoughtful investment decisions.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Rahul Perumal';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.3, major = 'Business Management', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/nyacohen/', why_hillside = 'I''m interested in Hillside Ventures because of the hands-on experience and learning I''ll receive about venture capital. As a business major and someone who has started a personal business, I''m excited to not only learn on how to help other companies and the aspects that go into making a marketable and profitable business, but also being able to apply these learning to my own business and professional goals. Additional, I want to be able to help other students learn about Hillside and their mission, empowering students to join Hillside, coming from someone who struggled to find opportunities like Hillside Ventures on Campus. Overall, I hope to grown my skills and gain real-world experience through Hillside.', contribution = 'As a business major and entrepreneur, I bring a strong interest and desire to learn and grow consumer product based companies in the real-world. Going beyond the Funds in class goals, I want to be able to contribute in helping bring a more inclusive and welcoming environment within the Genesis Fund. As someone who has questioned if I''ve belonged in certain spaces, I want to be the visible proof for students who may feel underrepresented, showing that they do belong here. I hope I can not only help support the Genesis Fund grow and help spread their mission goal, I also hope to help with the Funds mission on bringing more inclusivity and make Hillside more accessible to other students across campus.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Nya Cohen';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.8, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/matt-spector-297a84319', why_hillside = 'I choose to apply to Hillside because I am going to be an investment banker and in doing so, I strive myself on learning everything I can about the financial market through online resources. However, human experience always triumphs anything read online, which is why I now strive to enter into the Hillside program. I want to use this amazing opportunity as a way to finally receive hands on experience on communicating with clients, analyzing specific markets, talking with real business owners, and learn everything I can from this program. Not only would I be receiving valuable hands-on experience, but this is an opportunity to network with fellow classmates who are interested in the same interests as I am. Joining Hillside would be a major step towards the direction I am currently in, giving me a competitive advantage over an already highly competitive field. Additionally, Hillsides main two vertical only continued to incentivize me to join. Meeting with members from both the sustainability and financial technology verticals gave me insights on the frequency of deals as well as their quality. After many conversations and deep thought I have realized that financial technology aligns more with my interests especially the wealth tech and personal finance sector within the financial technology vertical which I am most interested in. With all of these factors I have no doubt in my mind the opportunity Hillside presents and whether next semester or the semester after that I will join Hillside, I will not give up on this great opportunity. Thank you.', contribution = 'I will contribute to the Genesis fund through two main factors. Deal frequency and leadership. Since Hillside is a competitive and exclusive opportunity, I will not take it for granted. Besides being an effective and active student within the class, I will personally be looking for a deal and adding to the deal frequency. My main goal in hillside is to get as much experience and knowledge as possible; in doing so I will make a deal to the board of investors to gain that experience of going all the way. I am not looking to be a sidelined player at Hillside; I am looking to push as many deals as I can to the top to maximize the amount of experience I can gain. Many of the conversations that I have had with current members I have noticed that a majority of the reasons that members have joined a specific vertical was due to either the deal frequency or how broad one vertical is over the other. I believe that a change should be made to the verticals that would better disperse this concentration of deals in sustainability and financial technology. This would not only allow for greater participation among vertical members but also give a smooth and less aggressive opportunity cost for new members when deciding on which vertical to join. I believe streamlining this change not only in just the Genisis fund but as well as the stem fund will boost the efficiency and deal frequency across all verticals.  

 Secondly, I will be taking a leadership role at the latest availability, I know they are given to third semester students, but the leadership can always use some help, which is where I will come in. I will be a member who can be counted on to get things done, and who is always available to help and lead. I will not only be a leader within the class, but I will have to portray leadership while being in charge of my own deals keeping a timely schedule as well as helping members who are on my deal.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Matthew Spector';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.4, major = 'finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jocelyn-pumayugra', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures appeals to me because it offers the kind of responsibility and real world exposure that prepares students for competitive finance careers. I am motivated to develop strong investment judgment, deepen my understanding of venture capital, and learn how to evaluate companies with both discipline and creativity in a financial spectrum.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a strong willingness to learn, solid analytical skills, and genuine interest in early stage startups. As a Finance major, I have learned how to evaluate risk, understand financial statements, and think critically about business models, and I am excited to apply that knowledge outside of the classroom. I am especially interested in financial innovation and human development because I believe access to financial tools and opportunities can make a real difference in people’s lives.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Jocelyn Pumayugra';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jackson-cafarella/', why_hillside = 'I am eager to join Hillside Ventures because of my strong interest in venture capital and my desire for hands-on, real-world finance experience. Hillside is more than just a club, it’s a venture fund that allows its analysts to work with real founders and real capital, which will allow me to develop skills that translate to both internships and future careers. Additionally, finance is a very broad field, and Hillside would give me valuable exposure to the world of valuation and investing. I am actively gaining experience in the realm of corporate and strategic finance through UConn’s Case Club, so being an analyst at Hillside would give me a comprehensive understanding of what careers are out there, and which ones best suit me. Finally, I have a genuine passion for sustainability, and I would love to explore startups that will not only provide financial returns, but also sustainable solutions that will help build a brighter future. I want to leave UConn knowing that I contributed to something impactful, and Hillside is the perfect way for me to do so.', contribution = 'I am confident in my ability to contribute to the Genesis Fund due to my academic achievements, demonstrated work ethic, and commitment to sustainability. In my first semester at UConn, I earned a 4.0 GPA, was named to the Dean’s List, and took relevant courses in math, economics, AI literacy, and climate change. In addition, I earned the Bloomberg ESG certificate, which gave me an understanding of how ESG metrics contribute to financial risk, and this is particularly relevant to the mission of the Genesis Fund. However, my work ethic is evident through not just my accomplishments in class, but also through my involvement at UConn. I am a member of the Business Connections Learning Community, Finance Society, Case Club, and I am a worker at Whitney Dining Hall, which demonstrates my ability to manage multiple commitments while remaining a reliable contributor. I also participated in a stock pitch competition, which gave me the opportunity to do extensive company research and enhance my presentation skills. Being part of the Genesis Fund would allow me to channel my discipline and willingness to learn into supporting startups that drive both financial performance and positive change.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Jackson Cafarella';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.96, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/filip-ciganik/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures is unlike any school organization I have seen before. It is a program that gives students real-life experience in the collaborative college setting. Growing up, I was always interested in Venture Capital and, I would read a lot about it online, so I have some prior experience.', contribution = 'I have been doing VITA so far this semester, and that has been an extraordinary experience. Learning how to communicate and help real people with their taxes has been a learning experience as I figure out how to use all the software. VITA has made me think on my feet and taught me how to communicate. Going to the Genesis Fund, I have already been reading online about Venture Capital Firms, I have some background experience.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Filip Ciganik';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.43, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/andre-larochelle-iv/', why_hillside = 'As a current freshman and rising sophomore, I believe Hillside Ventures represents an great opportunity for a student like me. As I continue to explore potential career paths after college, I see Hillside as a chance to gain meaningful insight into what it’s like to work in a competitive and professional environment. Additionally, collaborating with individuals who challenge me intellectually will help me develop new skills, push myself toward success, and grow both personally and professionally. 

Being surrounded by driven, like_minded students would motivate me to follow their example while expanding my experience and strengthening my network. Beyond that, I am greatly interested in Hillside’s mission of investing in companies that are working to solve real-world problems. Engaging directly with founders about their goals and motivations would not only sharpen my communication skills but also help me better understand the investor''s perspective within venture capital. 

One of my long-term goals is to eventually take over my father’s company. Gaining exposure to both sides of the industry (entrepreneurship and investing) would greatly enhance my understanding of what investors prioritize and how successful companies position themselves. 

Overall, I believe Hillside Ventures can help shape my path forward, offering the professional and academic growth I seek while providing valuable guidance from an experienced team.', contribution = 'My vertical of interest is Consumer Products. I recently learned that it is a new vertical replacing Human Development, which I had originally planned to join. I believe Consumer Products is an excellent fit for me because it offers the chance to explore products that can positively impact human well_being, whether through improved nutrition or overall health care. With a family history of health challenges linked to poor dietary habits, this vertical resonates with me personally and motivates me to identify companies focused on helping consumers break those patterns. 

It also provides the opportunity to discover brands that address diverse skin and hair_care needs. Although the market for these products is highly competitive, I am confident that my strong work ethic and commitment to thorough research will help me find companies that truly stand out, contributing to meaningful investment decisions for Hillside. 

By joining the Genesis Fund, I can offer an additional set of eyes and hands to support the team in securing deals that strengthen our portfolio. I take pride in being a quick learner with a coachable mindset, enabling me to produce efficient, high_quality work and conduct diligent analysis. 

In the end, my goal within this vertical is to uncover companies with memorable stories. Ones not only reflected in their products but also in the lives of the consumers they serve.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Andre LaRochelle';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.92, major = 'Finance/Analytics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/collin-murray-969487295/', why_hillside = 'I want to be part of Hillside Ventures because the hands-on experience working with venture capital can''t be learned in the classroom, it can only be gained through practice. I''m particularly interested in venture capital because I''d enjoy sourcing and analyzing companies and picking them apart while working with a team of like-minded, driven, and determined individuals. That one reason alone could be the most important reason of all for wanting to be part of Hillside Ventures, but I also want to apply my finance and analytical learning from the classroom to analyze and evaluate these startups. There are many valuable skills to be learned through the full deal process in Hillside, such as sourcing, memo writing, and pitching, that you won''t learn in a typical classroom setting. Hillside opens the door to so many opportunities that other students aren''t able to take advantage of, and being part of Hillside would give me the chance to make the most of them and set myself up for success further down the line. With that being said, Hillside Ventures interests me in particular because of the learning you don''t see in a typical classroom, working with driven peers who take investing seriously, and setting myself up for future success in this real-world environment.', contribution = 'I would be able to contribute to the Genesis Fund for several reasons. I bring a lot of valuable skills, qualities, and experiences to the team I am on and the program as a whole. As a junior finance major, I have built a strong foundation in valuation, financial statement analysis, and equity research through coursework, group projects, and the Opportunity Fund Project. I also believe I bring strong financial modeling and excel skills through coursework and I add structured thinking when building investment memos. I also bring relevant hands-on experience from last summer. I interned at PDC Brands, where I worked with financial data and supported operational decision making on the finance team. That experience strengthened my attention to detail and my ability to work with large data sets. However, outside of coursework and finance related topics, I believe I would be a strong fit for the Genesis Fund, as I am a strong team player. Outside of the classroom, I am very involved in Greek life at UConn, serving as president of my 100-person fraternity in 2025, earning president of the year honors, and being recognized nationally by our organization. This rule taught me a ton about leadership, public speaking, and emotional intelligence, which I think all play into being a positive team member and player. And since ending my tenure as president, I have stepped into the role of vice president and Community Impact in the Interfraternity Council, where I sit on an executive board with five other individuals overseeing 15 chapters and thousands of students. In addition, I would bring high accountability and maintain clear communication with teammates, while also putting in the time and effort to succeed in this program.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Collin Murray';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-del-sesto/', why_hillside = 'I’m drawn to Hillside Ventures because I genuinely enjoy investing, and venture capital offers exposure to private companies that are often inaccessible to the average investor. Coming from an equities background, I’ve learned to evaluate companies by breaking down their business models, competitive advantages, and growth drivers. Hillside Ventures allows me to apply that same framework to startup companies, which are earlier-stage and require a deeper focus on qualitative factors like market opportunity, product differentiation, and execution. Being part of Hillside Ventures would let me build on my equity research skill set while gaining hands-on experience evaluating high-growth companies at a different point in their lifecycle.', contribution = 'I believe I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a strong work ethic and an investor’s mindset to the fintech vertical. Through my personal investing experience and my experience in the Opportunity Fund Project, I’ve developed the habit of analyzing companies by breaking down business models, understanding revenue drivers, and identifying what creates long-term competitive advantage. That perspective translates well to venture capital and specifically fintech, where it’s critical to understand not just the product, but how the business scales and generates sustainable returns. I’m motivated to dive deeply into companies, learn from and be challenged by my peers, and contribute thoughtful, investment-driven analysis that helps the fund make well-informed decisions.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Michael Del Sesto';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.81, major = 'Major(s): Accounting, Chinese; Minor: Analytics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/hannah-krause2027', why_hillside = 'I want to learn more about venture capital, and Hillside Ventures looks like a wonderful opportunity to gain hands-on experience in the world of investing.', contribution = 'I would best be able to contribute to the Genesis Fund by examining the tax implications of the investments: Tax is a key factor in any business decision (including investments) that can significantly impact the success of a business.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Hannah Krause';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.3, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/malachievans/', why_hillside = 'I’m drawn to Hillside Ventures because it gives students real responsibility in evaluating and allocating capital, not just learning theory. Genesis particularly interests me because it operates at the earliest stage of company development, where disciplined thinking matters most. At that level, outcomes are driven by market size, founder quality, unit economics, and business model durability, the same core principles that underpin long-term investing in public equities.

I want to sharpen my ability to assess scalability, capital efficiency, and downside risk before a company reaches maturity. Hillside provides the structured environment, collaborative debate, and real capital allocation decisions that mirror professional investment teams. It’s the ideal setting to develop as a thoughtful, fundamentals-driven investor.', contribution = 'I would contribute both analytically and personally.

From a technical standpoint, I bring structured thinking. I enjoy breaking down business models into their core drivers, understanding where margins come from, and asking whether growth is truly scalable or simply capital-fueled. I’m comfortable working through financial assumptions, sizing markets thoughtfully, and building investment theses that balance upside with risk.

But more importantly, I bring character.

I’m not applying to Genesis to add a line to my resume. I’m genuinely trying to become excellent at capital allocation. I understand that venture is uncertain, humbling work, and I’m prepared for that. I’m resilient, receptive to feedback, and willing to do the unglamorous diligence work that often gets overlooked. I ask questions, I listen closely, and I absorb information like a sponge.

I care about being in rooms where ideas are debated seriously. I care about improving. And I care about contributing to a team that makes thoughtful, disciplined decisions with real capital.

Genesis represents an opportunity to learn the right way, collaboratively, rigorously, and with accountability, and I would approach it with humility, work ethic, and long-term commitment.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Malachi Evans';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.87, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jaden-c-king18-', why_hillside = 'What makes Hillside especially exciting to me is the chance to work in an environment where students aren’t just learning concepts like a regular class but are applying them to real investment decisions. Venture capital and Hillside''s focus on early-stage companies catches my interest as it requires looking past just numbers, considering people, ideas, and long-term potential which has been the spark for my interest in Finance. There is so much more to Finance then just scanning financial statements and Hillside feels like the natural next step to keep challenging myself in that way.  

Hillside also resonates with my long-term goal to pursue a career in asset management. In that field, you need both strong quantitative/analytical skills and a deep understanding of how to assess risk, market trends, management teams, and business potential. Hillside offers early exposure to that kind of work: building investment theses, doing due diligence, evaluating startups, preparing memos, and presenting to decision-makers. I believe this experience will help me transition smoothly into roles where I’m analyzing public or private assets, building portfolios, or making recommendations.  

Finally, I value how Hillside emphasizes learning across disciplines/verticals and includes students from various majors. That diversity of background, in my experiences, leads to stronger investment discussions, with different viewpoints and approaches to problems. Hillside’s culture of mentorship and collaboration, combined with its real decision-making focus, makes it an ideal place for me to grow while also contributing to a team working toward shared goals.', contribution = 'I think I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a mix of analytical skills, teamwork, 
and a willingness to learn. Through experiences like the HP Tech Ventures externship that I 
am currently enrolled in and UConn’s stock pitch competitions, I’ve had the chance to practice evaluating companies based on an investment thesis, analyzing financial  statements, and presenting investment ideas in a collaborative setting. These opportunities have given me a solid foundation in research and financial analysis that I am 
eager to apply to the work of the Fund. Additionally, in my role as a Student Administrative Specialist in the UConn Marketing Department, I’ve also strengthened my data analysis skills by working with datasets, organizing information, and supporting data-driven decision making.

What draws me particularly to the Genesis Fund is the chance to work directly with student-led investments while learning from peers who share a passion for finance. The  Fund provides a unique environment where passion and collaboration come together not only to develop investment strategies, but also to support one another’s career growth. In most of the positions/projects I have had, I find that active collaboration is something that both opens my eyes to new perspectives and also allows me to sharpen my peers. I am excited by the idea of contributing to that environment, where I can bring my own questions, perspectives, and research while also helping others build on their skills. The opportunity to be part of a team that balances responsibility with exploration is what makes the Genesis Fund meaningful to me.  

For me, joining the Genesis Fund is a combination of contribution and personal growth. I would bring the skills I have developed so far, but more importantly, I would approach the work with persistence, collaboration, and a commitment to supporting the team and the Fund’s goals.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Jaden King';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.72, major = 'Accounting major minor undecided', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/shubham-chandra-79a164278/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures stands out to me the most above any other club because it offers the opportunity to invest real capital into startups that may become the next big thing. As an accounting major, I want to use what I learned and analyze financial statements and assess the opportunity a company has to be successful in a wide market. Hillside would allow me to apply those skills in the seed stages of a company, which fits the dynamic I want to invest the most amount of time in. 

I''m also just drawn to simply working in a large team together. After going to some of the info sessions and meeting a lot of the analysts, everyone in Hillside Ventures sounds really motivated to work and willing to help newcomers. These are all dynamics of a group I want to be a part of. Finally, the hands-on nature of the Genesis Fund really interests me. Sourcing deals, building investment memos, and presenting investment decisions are all things I can take into the real world where I will have to be in a CPA firm or working in private equity, where I''d be doing these same things.

Ultimately, Hillside Ventures has everything that id want to join such a prestigious organization.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund because of my background information about venture capital. I know that venture capital is taking a small company, investing in its seed stages, and hoping for amazing investments in return. When looking at a company, the three major things that need to be assessed are whether they have a problem, a solution to that problem, and how much of the market they can take up for it to be sustainable for us to invest in.  I know about different terms for Venture capital. Things like TAM(total market for production, SAM(percentage I can get), and SOM (the target of how much of a portion of the market we are trying to get). Knowing these things and more gives me a good background of what I know.

On top of this, I feel like I can analyze the company''s finances well. My internship at Kirkles and Kotadis'' private CPA firm in Long Island, New York, helped me reconcile financial statements using accounting software like Accounting Power. There, I read companies'' balance sheets and income statements, and help finalize the business financial statements. I could use what I learned and apply it to Hillside Ventures, where you have to analyze a company''s financial statements in order to decide to invest in the business. 

Finally, as a person im very friendly to approach. I love making friends and having people included in conversations. I was captain of my Varsity soccer team, where I learned how to lead a group of people. Things I feel like I could implement into Hillside Ventures. Above all, I want to make genuine friends in Hillside and help people so our team dynamic can be amazing.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Shubham Chandra';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.84, major = 'Finance/Analytics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/sahil-sheik/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures was originally recommended to me by my advisor, and although I did not join finance for venture capital originally, it is a field that I have been increasingly drawn to. I want to join Hillside because of the real world experience I would gain from the program, and also because I am very interested in venture capital. 

Venture Capital is a high risk, high reward industry, and that draws me in. In Hillside, I would have a chance to source businesses, talk to them, and if approved, real money would be invested in exchange for a stake in the business. If the business fails, however, then the money is gone. I want to learn how to choose good businesses to invest in, and those skills would be transferrable to other fields in finance. 

Hillside will also teach me skills transferrable to other fields in finance. Even if a business’s pitch deck looks good, I need to be able to pick it apart and see how the company is really doing. Doing that is also required in other fields of finance, such as mergers and acquisitions. Investing in a company just because the pitch deck looks good is not a good strategy.  

Another reason I want to join Hillside is because I get to meet different, passionate people. I get to see why they decided to start a business, and what drives them to keep building. Be it a personal experience or money, I get to see why people are building what they build. I also get to encounter a variety of ideas that solve problems I might not have known existed. Ideas that can have a real impact on the world. The prospect of being able to invest in those solutions and ideas is very interesting.   

Overall, Hillside would allow me to gain skills and real world experience in venture capital. This experience and these skills would also be useful in other fields, such as mergers and acquisitions. Hillside would also let me meet with passionate founders that have ideas that could have a real impact on the world, and I would have the ability to invest in those ideas with real money. I believe I am a great fit for Hillside Ventures.', contribution = 'I believe I can contribute to the Genesis fund with my knowledge, my passion for the verticals, and my willingness to learn. I was instantly drawn to both the Sports and Wellness and the Consumer Products verticals. Sports and Wellness really interests me. I consider myself an active person because I go to the gym and run. Being able to see all the new innovations in the field that might help improve performance or sports tracking would be really interesting. It’s an exciting prospect. The Consumer Products vertical also interests me due to its concentration on everyday products. There’s always a new innovation in the field. 

I realize that joining the Genesis fund means I will have to learn many things in a short time. I believe my willingness to learn will help me understand what I need to know and learn and use the skills I need. I would try my best to contribute from day one. 

Overall, I think my knowledge, passion, and willingness to learn would help me effectively contribute to the Genesis fund.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Sahil Sheik';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Analytics and Information Management', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-kaplan/', why_hillside = 'I’m drawn to Hillside Ventures because it offers early, hands-on exposure to venture capital. The Genesis Fund’s deal flow and investment committee process mean you’re working with real startups, not simulations. You’re not analyzing hypotheticals; you’re evaluating companies where decisions actually matter. Being in an environment where ideas are tested against founders and outcomes fits how I like to learn: by doing, taking responsibility, and building judgment through experience. In conversations with current members, that depth of experience consistently came up as formative, which reinforced my interest.

What excites me most is the learning environment and the skills it builds. Hillside pushes you to articulate and defend an investment vision clearly: explaining why a company matters, challenging assumptions in diligence, and refining ideas through real debate. You learn to communicate conviction while staying open to being wrong, which is a mindset I value a lot. The research carries real weight because it can directly influence an investment decision. I’m also drawn to the collaborative dynamic where members challenge each other, sharpen thinking, and elevate ideas together. That kind of environment builds both analytical strength and the ability to persuade and lead discussions.

I’ve already started developing this mindset through stock pitches and building analytics reports in the clubs I’m involved in, and Hillside feels like the place where that momentum compounds. It’s a chance to be around people who care deeply about execution and bold ideas, while bringing a data-driven lens to the evaluation of opportunities. More than exposure, I’m excited by the opportunity to actively participate in sourcing, diligence, and decision-making, and keep sharpening how I think about investing. Hillside feels like the kind of place where you don’t just learn venture, you start becoming an investor.', contribution = 'As an incoming analyst, the most important thing I would contribute to the Genesis Fund is execution. The fund only works when analysts are willing to do the real work: sourcing opportunities, digging into companies, and following through with thoughtful research. I take accountability seriously in the environments I’m part of, and I would bring a disciplined, high-effort approach to diligence. Whether that means going deeper on market research, validating assumptions, or doing the extra work behind a thesis, I want to be someone the fund can rely on when decisions require real effort and follow-through.

I would also contribute by bringing independent thinking into investment discussions. In early-stage environments, it’s easy for group sentiment to shape decisions, but I approach opportunities with a clear and unbiased lens. If I believe a company has strong fundamentals, whether through market potential, founder team, or a strong exit strategy, I’m standing by that view while still staying open-minded to being challenged. My goal is to contribute honest conviction, not consensus thinking, and help ensure that decisions are driven by reasoning rather than momentum.

Finally, I would contribute through relationship-driven sourcing and judgment. I value building real conversations with founders and using those interactions to sanity-check opportunities early. Strong deal flow is not just about quantity, but about filtering for quality, and I would focus on bringing in opportunities that are thoughtful and well-vetted. I naturally gravitate toward connecting with people and reading signals beyond the surface, and I would use that strength to help source credible opportunities and support more confident decision-making across the fund. Overall, I want to be someone who contributes execution, independent thinking, and high-quality sourcing to the Genesis Fund.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Oliver Kaplan';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://linkedin.com/in/cole-ostrosky', why_hillside = 'Through my first semester at UConn I have come to realize that the reason I am here is because of all of the opportunities. Through the various opportunities, students have the chance to get real world experiences before they leave the classroom. However, not all opportunities offer this bonus, there are a select few that give you the experience needed to change a student from school ready to job ready. One of those organizations is Hillside Ventures. I found out about Hillside Ventures after it was too late to apply last semester, and have been curious about it since. So I attended information sessions, and had multiple coffee chats, and now I am writing my application. Through the information sessions and coffee chats, I found out just how much I didn’t know. I realized that there are certain qualities in applicants that come from experience alone. For example, in information session two there was a run through of how to analyze a company''s Pitch Deck. Now I could tell that some of the information on the slides was good, however there were details that I didn’t catch. For example, why did Earth Grid show that they had two different streams of revenue? The first thought in my head was “If one stream weakens, they will still have another”, but the answer was actually that BADASS was more of a one time revenue stream, and BOOM was a long-term cashflow, which shows investors that the company will continue to make money off of single installments of the product over a long period of time. My point is, Hillside Ventures is an amazing opportunity to learn from real world experience. Talk to real companies, invest real money, do real research, everything in the job of an analyst will prepare me for the real world.', contribution = 'I have some experience due to stock pitch competitions. Stock pitches give you a couple skills, such as being able to conduct valuable research, do comparative analysis, and give effective presentations. I believe these skills will be able to help me in a venture capitalist scene because venture capitalists require lots of research on different companies to determine if they are worth pursuing. Once you decide you would like to pursue the stock, you have to be able to compare it to the industry, competition, etc. Finally, you have to be able to wrap it all together with a presentation. I understand these are just a few of the skills needed for venture capitalists, but I believe they will give me the groundwork I need to get started. and the ability to give effective presentations. The vertical I am applying for is sustainability. I am particularly interested in sustainability because I believe it is the future. Hillside defines sustainability as, “companies that address environmental, social, and economic crises by providing sustainable solutions and/or mitigating factors that inhibit sustainability”, environmental, social, and economic crises happen consistently over time, and solutions to these will be the future. My interest began to be peaked by sustainability when I pitched Micron Technology (MU), and further when I pitched Nextpower (NXT). Micron focuses on the semiconductor industry, and Nextpower on the solar power industry. Learning about these companies made me realize that they are the future. Semiconductors for AI, and solar power will be everywhere. Other than my experience, I am willing. I will be willing to show up every day and learn as much as I can. I will be willing to put in the hours I need to get everything done both well and on time. I am willing to try new things and take advice from people.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Cole Ostrosky';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.95, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/willcurry14', why_hillside = 'I am drawn to Hillside Ventures because it offers the unique opportunity to invest in real companies and have a real-world impact while still at UConn. That level of responsibility creates higher stakes and a “learn by doing” environment that I believe I could thrive in. I am excited about the chance to understand how early-stage businesses operate in practice. I want to see how their early processes form, how they analyze markets, how they make strategic and financial decisions with limited resources, and how they move from an idea to a functioning and scalable company. The ability to learn and experience these things firsthand by working with founders is something that I think will help me no matter what I pursue after my UConn career. Being part of Hillside would let me build practical skills in financial and market analysis while also strengthening my communication, public speaking, and critical thinking in a setting where the work has real consequences. I am looking for an experience where I can both contribute and be pushed to think deeply about how businesses succeed, and Hillside offers that.

          I am especially interested in the Sports and Wellness vertical because it connects directly to my own life and interests. I grew up playing sports, have spent many months in physical therapy, and currently I am very focused on weightlifting and health optimization, so I have been around this space for a long time and naturally follow new ideas and companies in it. Because of that background, the chance to help identify and support a startup that could genuinely improve how people train, recover, prevent injuries, or live healthier lives is something I find very motivating. I also took the time to speak with several current Hillside members and what stood out most to me was the culture and the strong relationships people build through the organization. Everyone I spoke with described a collaborative environment where students take the work seriously but also support each other and stay connected even after their time in the fund ends. That combination of real investing experience, meaningful skill development, alignment with my interests, and a strong community is why I want to be part of Hillside Ventures.', contribution = 'I believe I can contribute to the Genesis Fund first and foremost by being someone who learns quickly, takes initiative, and is fully committed to getting up to speed as fast as possible. If selected, I would treat the time before next semester as a chance to learn everything I can about Hillside’s process, past investments, and evaluation framework so I can hit the ground running. I approach new environments with the mindset that I should listen first, absorb as much as possible, and then contribute as best I can, and I would carry that same approach throughout my time in the fund. Over the past year I have built strong outreach and communication skills through my role as Zeta Psi’s HuskyTHON coordinator and through extensive networking during my internship search. I have completed more than a dozen professional interviews over the past few months, which has made me comfortable speaking with experienced teams over Zoom, preparing thoughtful questions, and keeping conversations structured and productive. I believe that experience would translate directly into helping conduct smooth, professional founder calls and representing Hillside well in external communications.

          Academically, I am in a position where I can commit serious time and energy to the Genesis Fund. As a sophomore with 100 credits completed or in progress, I am ahead in my coursework and have taken or am currently taking business and finance classes that strengthen my ability to analyze companies, understand financials, and evaluate strategic decisions. Because of my advanced credit status, I have more flexibility to dedicate meaningful time to Hillside compared to many other students, and I would use that flexibility to give my all to this fund. Finally, the Sports and Wellness vertical sits directly at the intersection of my personal background and interests, as well as my professional passion for finance and business development. Having grown up playing sports and now being deeply engaged in weightlifting and health optimization, the sports and wellness vertical targets a space that I am already very familiar with. That personal connection means I would bring genuine energy, curiosity, and long-term commitment to contributing as much as I can to the Genesis fund.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Will Curry';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.44, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/sara-s-b31b242a0', why_hillside = 'One of the things that initially drew me to Hillside Ventures is its one of the very few opportunities where the stakes are real and your decisions will play a direct role in your investments.  While there are workshops and simulations that mimic the business world, they don''t acknowledge the risks or consequences of one''s actions. Hillside venture analysts source deals and make investment decisions using real money, a $1 million fund where outcome actually matters. It allows me to have hands on experience and apply everything I''ve learned from different classes. Hillside allows for group focused work, gaining expertise over time as you move forward with decisions and see the fruits of your labor on whether a portfolio company will grow or struggle based on the decisions the team made. I''m also drawn to the culture Hillside offers, being around passionate analysts across different majors who are choosing to be there to work towards a common mission. This collaborative dynamic will help me grow as well as develop as a leader by thinking sharper and moving meaningfully.', contribution = 'I believe I can contribute to the Genesis Fund sustainability team through both my financial background and hands on teamwork experience. As a Finance major who''s taken econometrics, accounting, and statistics, I have developed my critical thinking skills as well as the ability to weigh risk when it comes to making decisions. This really matters for sustainability because companies often operate with longer time horizons before actually making a profit. I also completed a Universitas 21 micro-internship where I worked with a global team to develop a plan advancing women''s education and employment in India in direct support of UN Sustainable Development Goal 8. I built tracking frameworks by drawing on research and implementations from neighboring countries that have implemented similar ideas, to develop real metrics and transportation plans aimed at connecting women in rural areas to education and employment opportunities, which is directly related to evaluating sustainability startups that want to create genuine change. Within this micro-internship, I was able to work and coordinate with members across the world to come up with reasonable solutions that acknowledge the social and cultural barriers in India, making sure it would work in practice. I also have experience managing teams and committees, fundraising, managing budgets, coordinating events, and doing more with minimal funds to maximize impact. Across these experiences, I''ve maintained consistency in my hard work and in collaborating towards something bigger than myself. I hope to bring that same commitment and passion, along with my experience, to the Hillside Ventures team.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Sara Shawahna';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.88, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/ranganathan-kidambi/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures’ unique research-driven approach, analytical rigor, and growth opportunities appeal to me. For one, Hillside invests in start-ups over established companies to boost growth and guide newer firms to success. I find this intriguing as it encourages analysts to take a deep dive and explore businesses outside the mainstream. I am also excited by the challenge of evaluating companies without traditional metrics, as it combines both qualitative and quantitative perspectives to make decisions.

Furthermore, the process of sourcing deals and conducting due diligence aligns with my interests in data-driven decision-making and model creation. Through Finance Society stock pitches, I conducted market research, analyzed industries, and reviewed key growth drivers to construct valuation models. This perfectly translates to facilitating deal flow, preparing presentations, and drafting investment memos, all of which will be key at Hillside. Hillside’s methodical research process and unique discipline-driven strategies stand out. Exploring sustainable businesses on the frontier of climate solutions and technology-driven business improvements is a rare opportunity to participate in innovation.

Beyond the technical aspects, I also value Hillside’s culture of collaboration, mentorship, and commitment to improvement. What sets Hillside apart is the ability to work directly with industry experts, founders, and analysts, cultivating an encouraging environment. Teamwork at Hillside builds an environment where I know I will thrive. Although I gained some experience working in teams at a profitable start-up through Junior Achievement, Hillside Ventures takes these skills to the next level; its exposure to innovative founders, an experienced network of professionals, and a tight-knit group of talented analysts will present continued opportunities for learning and growth.

I also appreciate the amount of consideration that Hillside puts into its investments. The Consumer Products Vertical, which prioritizes companies focusing on food, beverages, care, and lifestyle, is something I am passionate about. Hillside’s recent deal progression on Veracity, a natural non-drug solution to weight management and competitor to GLP-1s, is incredibly innovative and inspiring. Such products are not only financially strong, but they also have the potential to change lives and raise the quality of life for many people. In the Sustainability Vertical, Hillside’s investment in EarthGrid demonstrates significant upside and is incredibly innovative. EarthGrid''s low-cost, rapid plasma boring technology has numerous applications and can revolutionize the transmission of electricity. These investments allow Hillside to be at the intersection of sustainable innovation and technological advancement. 

In this way, Hillside utilizes ESG investments to contribute to significant societal, environmental, and financial impacts. This opportunity deeply resonates with me and is one step closer to being part of world-changing innovation that I truly believe in.', contribution = 'My experience, work ethic, problem-solving ability, and eagerness to learn make me a strong candidate for Hillside Ventures. My unique skillset enables me to contribute to every stage of the investment process while continuing to learn and listen to new perspectives. 

As a VC Extern at HP Tech Ventures, I conduct due diligence on startup investments and work on synthesis reports for key business areas, including competitive landscapes, risk analyses, and growth catalysts. This directly translates to thoroughly researching companies, quick screens and one-pager evaluations, and building investment memos. 

Furthermore, as a UConn Finance Society stock pitch winner, I evaluated industry performance, identified key drivers of company success, and built valuation and comparative models to assess financial health. I gained hands-on experience incorporating new analyst recommendations, analyzing market data, and constructing DCF charts, which translates to the intensive research required for startup evaluation at Hillside. 

Job simulations with Fidelity International strengthened my ability to leverage market observations, assess risks, and validate financial projections. In addition, my role as an investment research trainee at The UConn Opportunity Fund Project will complement my learning of financial markets and risk evaluation. Overall, these critical skills are essential in analyzing businesses from multiple angles and constructing strong, evidence-based investment arguments.

Beyond technical analysis, I value collaboration and teamwork. As Vice President of Finance for DECA, I revamped the school-based enterprise’s business model by working with town representatives, vendors, and team members to improve operations. By introducing new products, strengthening accounting systems, and incorporating diverse ideas, we increased sales by 300% and scaled our workforce by 150%. 

At Hillside Ventures, I will contribute both through technical work–whether that includes writing investment memos, monitoring deal flow, and providing strategic guidance–and through cultivating a welcoming environment where every perspective is valued.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Ranganathan Kidambi';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/pristine-ruhuma/', why_hillside = 'My name is Pristine Ruhuma, and I am a freshman finance major from West Hartford, CT. I think that Hillside is one of the best opportunities available on campus for any aspiring business professional. I have always had an interest in the business world and making investments of my own. I love that at Hillside, I can build on this interest. Being able to use real money and be a part of a venture capital fund, and to be able to collaborate with others, intrigues me. At Hillside, I have the opportunity to be mentored by professors with industry expertise while gaining professional experience of my own. Overall, Hillside allows me to gain professional experience in the finance industry while allowing me to explore my options and career paths for the future.', contribution = 'I think that I can contribute to Genesis in many ways. I am a good collaborator, I am a critical thinker, and I am determined. I have been a part of many teams, whether it be sports teams, research teams, teams at DECA competitions, or even stock market competitions. In many of these teams, I have conducted extensive research, working with others who share similar interests. In the Genesis Fund, I would also be added to one of the diligence groups of Sustainability, Sports & Wellness, Consumer Products, or Financial Technology. As a part of these groups, we would research the market to gauge which businesses are best to be invested in. My research experience would add value to whichever group I am placed in. My research experience has vastly improved my critical thinking skills, and if I am not as knowledgeable in a certain industry, I am willing to put the work in to learn and analyze. I want to help solve problems, and I want to use my research to analyze specific markets and help these start-ups. My drive and work ethic will also be a great addition, as once I find an interest, I am determined to act on it. If you give me a problem, I will not stop until I can solve it. Considering everything, I believe I would be a great addition to the Genesis Fund''s team.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Pristine Ruhuma';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.94, major = 'Finance & Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/vedika-patel/', why_hillside = 'Hillside stands out to me because it gives students the opportunity to learn how to invest and understand what investors look for when evaluating companies, which is something I have always wanted to explore further. I am applying specifically to the Genesis Fund because it focuses on developing analytical and financial skills through real-world investment experience. As an economics student at UConn, I want to deepen my understanding of how financial decisions are made and how to evaluate companies from an investor’s perspective. While learning these skills in the classroom is very important, putting them into practice is a major part of what drew me to Hillside. In addition, being part of a team made up of highly driven students is something I have always wanted to be involved in. I believe Hillside provides a close-knit community where members support one another while sharing a strong interest in finance and investing. Working with motivated individuals will challenge me to grow and allow me to learn from those around me. Through the Genesis Fund, I hope to gain hands-on experience, strengthen my financial knowledge, and apply what I learn in the classroom to real-world investment opportunities. Most importantly, I plan to contribute to a team that emphasizes collaboration, curiosity, and professional growth.', contribution = 'I will be able to contribute to the Genesis Fund through my collaborative mindset and creative approach to problem-solving. I enjoy working with others to exchange ideas and learn from one another. As an economics and finance major, I have developed analytical and research skills that will be beneficial to the Genesis Fund, especially when evaluating companies and identifying investment opportunities. I am particularly interested in consumer goods companies, as I enjoy analyzing how brand positioning, pricing strategy, and evolving consumer demand impact long-term profitability and competitive advantage, while remaining open to exploring businesses across other industries. During my internship at Comfort Inn, I gained hands-on experience analyzing business performance and understanding how management decisions affect overall profitability. This experience strengthened my ability to interpret data and think critically, all of which are skills that directly apply to investment analysis. I also bring curiosity and enthusiasm for learning, which helps me stay engaged and open to feedback from both peers and mentors. I believe my ability to communicate effectively and work well in a team setting will allow me to contribute meaningfully to the Genesis Fund. I am confident that I can add value to the Fund’s investment research and discussions.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Vedika Patel';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.84, major = 'Major: Finance/Minor: History', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/theodoremitchell', why_hillside = 'Since arriving at UConn, Hillside Ventures has stood out to me as the most impactful student organization on campus. What makes it truly unique is the opportunity to invest real money into real companies, specifically at the pre-seed to Series A stage, where the stakes and learning are highest. I feel investing at this stage demands more than just having strong financial analysis; it requires the foresight to evaluate a company not just in its current form, but through the full arc of its growth towards their eventual exit strategy. That kind of long-term thinking is rare to develop at the undergraduate level, and it’s exactly the skill set I want to develop more of. Beyond the investing experience itself, I am drawn to the communal sense Hillside fosters. An environment where ambitious peers push each other to work harder, be better, and grow beyond what they thought was possible. For those reasons, Hillside is not just an organization I want to join, it is one I want to grow with and help shape into its best possible version.', contribution = 'I feel I can bring an interesting and unique viewpoint and hunger to the Genesis Fund. On my own, I have been investing in the stock market for around five years. This has given me hands-on experience analyzing financial statements, understanding business models, and developing my own unique investment perspective that goes beyond the surface level. I don''t take things at face value, and I make sure to dig deeper, a habit I would bring to the Genesis Fund when sourcing and evaluating companies for the fund.

Beyond my investing background, I feel the work I put into securing my upcoming internship at Corbin Advisors speaks to the kind of effort I bring to the things I truly care about. Landing that role was not a matter of simply submitting an application. I made sure to thoroughly research them, understand their advisory model, and know exactly who I was walking into a conversation with before I ever sat down for an interview. I listened carefully, asked genuine questions, and showed up as someone who had done their homework. That level of preparation is not something I do to check a box; it is just how I operate when something matters to me. It is the same approach I have taken with Hillside. When I applied previously, I unfortunately didn''t get accepted. Rather than being discouraged and not applying again, I took this rejection as an indirect gift and used the time to work on myself so I could present the best possible version of myself when the opportunity came around again. I attended multiple information sessions and coffee chats, and during each one I made sure to ask genuine questions, stay engaged, and absorbed as much information as I could. I would bring that same intentionality to every single deal I source, every founder I speak with, and every conversation I have on behalf of the Genesis Fund.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Theodore Mitchell';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Economics and Finance/Marketing and Realestate', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/roan-fothergill', why_hillside = 'Hillside will greatly contribute to my future career and increase my confidence and expertise in my professional dream. I have always been naturally drawn to finance, specifically venture capital. From creating my own clothing brand to investing in myself, I will consistently work to develop the skills needed to be self-sufficient. While most jobs have a clearly outlined salary path and end goal, venture capital requires you to bet on yourself and your own skills. 
I want to be able to bet on myself to succeed and continue learning, so I can translate that into professional success. Hillside Ventures’ knowledge and insight will not only refine my abilities in investment analysis and decision-making but will also allow me to move closer to my aspiration of becoming a full-time investor.', contribution = 'With the drive and passion, I already have, I will put my best work forward to analyze private companies in order to contribute returns on investments to Hillside Ventures. As an Economics and Finance major, I have some insight into analyzing companies, both through coursework and by managing my own portfolio. Combined with my genuine interest in investing, this knowledge will drive me to analyze and push deals forward the best I can.

My past experiences through internships and volunteering have helped develop my strong communication skills. These experiences have prepared me to be able to communicate consciously with founders and confidently seek advice and critique with confidence. I am committed to bringing rigorous analytical effort and a disciplined work ethic to the success of Hillside Ventures.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Roan Fothergill';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.73, major = 'Finance and Economics/Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jessicandjomou', why_hillside = 'I am interested in Hillside Ventures because I am seeking a beyond-the-classroom finance experience here on campus, and I strongly believe Hillside Ventures will provide just that. As a finance and economics student, I have been gaining an analytical foundation but would love to apply these skills in a more hand-on experience, as well as continue to grow my skillset. By being part of Hillside, it facilitates an environment and a delicate process where each step allows you to learn and develop important skills. I am eager to practice skills such as managing capital, fostering innovation, public speaking, and due diligence, which will allow me to grow both professionally and personally. 

Not only is Hillside a great opportunity to learn hands-on but also the chance to learn from experts, including fellow students/analysts, mentors, entrepreneurs, and professors. One aspect of Hillside that sticks out to me is the community. It an inclusive community where everyone wants to challenge and uplift each other in the most helpful way. This is an optimal setting for one to grow and excel as it allows you to think both tactically and creatively, furthering developing professional and public speaking skills. Overall Hillside Ventures offers an intellectually stimulating and inclusive environment, which I would love to contribute to.  

Overall with Hillside Ventures'' diverse portfolio and commitment to giving back to the School of Business, it is clear that the analysts are contributing to a meaningful experience. I am interested in being part of this opportunity where entrepreneurship and innovation are embraced, and long-term impact is made.', contribution = 'I will contribute to the Genesis Fund by embracing the experience and each step of the process. I am a firm believer that with everything you do, you benefit from what you put into it. My goal this past year has been to put myself out there professionally and network more. By reaching out to professionals, conducting coffee chats, and being part of a student-led mentorship program this past winter break, it has allowed me to grow my confidence with my interpersonal communication. I am eager to apply these professional skills in Hillside, especially when it comes to sourcing, conducting founders calls, and asking/answering questions. In addition to this, I will contribute an attentive mindset to the team. Through my academics and extracurriculars, I have experience working with data and financial modeling, which requires attention to detail and precision. With an eye for detail, I will bring a critical mindset when it comes to assessing startups, conducting due diligence, and memo writing. Lastly, as both a Finance and Economics major, not only am I coming in with a finance background but also with a deep understanding of economics as well. With my quantitative economics classes I have been practicing market and policy analysis. So, when it comes to looking at pitch decks and evaluating startups, I can approach my assessments through a market structure and consumer incentive lens. I strongly believe that my combination of financial and economic reasoning, along with my attention to detail and professionalism will allow me to contribute meaningfully to the Genesis Fund.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Jessica Ndjomou';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.9, major = 'Finance/Data Analytics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicolas-sconziano-22b960290/', why_hillside = 'For me, Hillside Ventures is another opportunity to gain real experience in a financial environment while at school. While interviewing for internships over the fall, I noticed I was missing experiences with real financial analysis and decision-making. I found it hard to draw on my internship (more of an operations role, but still some analysis) and class experiences for certain questions. This is one of the reasons I applied for the Opportunity Fund Project, and one of the main reasons I am applying for Hillside. 

Hillside Ventures will allow me to look at the buy-side from another angle, this time, as part of a venture capital firm. Instead of just looking at financial data to make investment decisions, Hillside will allow me the opportunity to meet founders, hear ideas, and gauge business potential from a company''s human capital. I feel that this is extremely important and sometimes overlooked when making investment decisions regarding larger companies. 

Finally, the analysis I would be doing, whether it is looking at financial statements or talking with founders, is something I would absolutely enjoy. The idea of being able to invest real money in a startup and watch it grow, knowing you made a contribution to that growth, however small, is something that would give me immense satisfaction.', contribution = 'I feel that my past experiences will help me contribute greatly to the Genesis Fund. The work I am doing this semester with the Opportunity Fund Project, as well as the work I am doing in my higher-level finance classes, can be easily transferred to the Genesis Fund. I have plenty of experience with financial analysis and understanding the meaning behind certain financial measurements, which I believe will be valuable to the Genesis Fund.

I also believe that my experience working in teams will make me a great asset to whichever vertical team I am staffed on. My time in sports, whether it be with UConn Baseball or my summer league team, has taught me how important a collective mindset and "pulling on the same rope" is. My past internship was also very team-based, and taught me just how important the dull or monotonous work is to overall team success. I am willing to do whatever work that will contribute to overall success, and whatever will make somebody else''s life easier, just like at my internship. 

Finally, I have plenty of interest in the Genesis Fund verticals. I am always paying attention to the latest advancements in sports and wellness, as well as advancements in FinTech, and AI in finance. I would also love to learn about the latest in sustainability and certain consumer products. I will bring this passion to whichever vertical I am staffed on.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Nicolas Sconziano';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.5, major = 'Dual Degree in Business Mangement and Economics of Sustainable Devolpment and Mangement', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/arfa-begum', why_hillside = 'I am interested in joining Hillside Ventures at UConn because I want to strengthen my understanding of business and entrepreneurship. I am passionate about building businesses that are not only financially successful, but also responsible and sustainable.

I am from Bangladesh, and agriculture has always been part of my family’s identity. My father and his family grew up on agricultural land that is still a part of their lives today. Growing up, I always heard stories from my father about farming, harvest seasons, and the hard work it takes to live off the land. That connection shaped the way I see food, sustainability, and community, and it ultimately influenced my decision to pursue my second degree.

At the same time, I am aware that Bangladesh, like many parts of South Asia, faces challenges with unethical labor practices and environmental strain within agriculture. Farmers often work hard without fair compensation, and sustainability is not always prioritized in larger supply chains. Seeing both the beauty of my family’s agricultural roots and the reality of these systemic issues has shaped my personal and career goals.

In the future, I want to create a South Asian coffee shop that celebrates our culture and traditions, but does so responsibly. Through my future small business, I hope to share my culture in a meaningful way while also being part of the solution. My goal is to source ingredients ethically, support farmers directly when possible, and prioritize sustainability in every decision I make. I know that as a business owner, I will be responsible for major decisions such as where to source coffee beans and tea leaves, which suppliers to invest in, and how to balance cost with ethical standards. For me, this business would not just be about running a coffee shop; it would be about honoring where I come from and contributing to a future where agricultural practices in South Asia are more ethical, transparent, and environmentally conscious.

Along with that, I hope to build my coffee shop to be truly sustainable in every aspect. During my study abroad in London, I had the opportunity to visit the European Bank, and I was inspired by both their building design and their business values. Their entire building was constructed using recycled and repurposed materials, and for anything that was not, they already had plans in place to recycle it after its use. Even the window blinds were made from recycled materials.

Seeing how intentional they were about sustainability changed the way I think about business. It showed me that sustainability can be built into the foundation of a company. That visit strengthened my vision for my future coffee shop. I want it to operate as a fully sustainable and recycling-focused business, modeled after the European Bank’s commitment to environmental responsibility.

Through Hillside Ventures, I hope to gain the practical knowledge and strategic skills to run a successful business. More importantly, I want to understand how to evaluate investments, conduct strong business research, and make informed financial decisions. I believe Hillside will give me the foundation to understand long-term sustainability from both an ethical and financial perspective. The opportunity to learn from experienced entrepreneurs and apply business concepts in real-world settings would prepare me to make responsible decisions when building my future coffee shop.', contribution = 'As a Leadership Legacy Scholar at UConn, I am part of a selective, year-long leadership development program made up of a small group of student leaders. Being in this program has helped me grow not just as a leader on campus, but as a leader after graduation. Through honest conversations, reflection, and collaboration, I have become more confident in my values and more intentional in how I lead others. Being surrounded by other motivated leaders has challenged me to think deeper, communicate more clearly, and step up with confidence. This experience has strengthened my ability to lead with purpose both now and in my future career.

Serving as President of the South Asian Women Empowerment Association for the past two years has further shaped my leadership style. In this role, I have learned how to manage a team with diverse perspectives, delegate responsibilities effectively, and foster a collaborative environment. I have also grown into a more confident public speaker and an active listener which I believe are skills that are essential when advocating for a mission and representing an organization. Leading meetings, planning large-scale events, and navigating challenges within an executive board have strengthened my adaptability and communication skills.

I hope to bring these leadership experiences into Genesis by contributing thoughtfully to discussions with peers and engaging meaningfully with business professionals. I am eager to both share my perspective and learn from others, continuing to refine my leadership approach in a business-focused environment.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Arfa Begum';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/cristianjimenez12/', why_hillside = 'What draws me to Hillside is the team environment. After having coffee chats with current members I could clearly see that this is not a place where people just show up and mind their own business like any other class. Everyone works together on deals, calls, and presentations pushing each other toward the same goal and that is the environment I want to surround myself with. Beyond that, what draws me to VC over other finance paths is the combination of analytical work and real human interaction because you are not just analyzing numbers you are also working directly with successful people looking to grow their business. Through VC you get to build real relationships with founders and that client facing dynamic genuinely excites me. Hillside is one of the few places where a first year student can experience all of that with real capital on the line.', contribution = 'Someone once told me "In venture capital you will fail a hundred times, but you need to show up for that hundred and first" because that might be the one that reaches the memo stage or even better a deal. That quote reflects who I am as a person. I am not someone who gives up easily, and in a fund that sources hundreds of deals per week just to pass one or two a semester, I believe my perseverance will be a real contribution to the Genesis Fund.
As a volleyball player and captain for over six years, I bring a genuine athlete''s perspective to the Sports and Wellness vertical that goes beyond stats because I have lived the gaps these companies are trying to solve. That combination of resilience and firsthand experience is what will allow me to connect with founders, understand their vision, and contribute meaningfully.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Cristian Jimenez';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.83, major = 'B.S in Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/evan-morrow-uconn-finance/', why_hillside = 'I think Hillside Venture is a unique opportunity for UConn students because it offers real exposure to venture capital in a hands_on, decision_making environment. Students aren’t just observing they’re sourcing startups and influencing actual investments. I would love to be part of the collaborative culture, gain exposure to founders, and contribute to a real investment fund that offers an external experience where I can grow, learn, and push myself beyond the traditional classroom environment.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a unique, multi_angled perspective shaped by my background in finance, accounting, and entrepreneurship. Through tax preparation, financial analysis coursework, and running a profitable youth lacrosse program, I’ve developed strong analytical discipline and real operating insight. This combination allows me to evaluate early-stage companies with both quantitative rigor and practical business judgment.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Evan Micheal Morrow';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.4, major = 'Major: Computer Science, Minor: Healthcare Management and Insurance Studies', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/riasverma/', why_hillside = 'For me, Hillside Ventures is an opportunity that stands out as it offers the exact intersection between my academic background in computer/data science and my growing interest in seeing the real-world impacts that startups and products have on customers (especially in the technology sector). As a Computer Science major, my coursework and personal projects have given me experience in hands-on problem solving, coding, analyzing data with modeling, and insight into some of the latest trends in the technology industry. However, as I think about my future career interests, I have become more interested in learning about how this rise in technology/AI translates into real value for customers and companies. Being a student and getting to look into real startups, communicate with stakeholders, evaluate them based on data, and decide whether to invest in them is an amazing opportunity for me to gain skills that can help develop me further for my future career. 

In my previous internship at Hartford HealthCare, I was exposed to the business and product side of technology for the first time. I found myself drawn to understanding customer and user experience, how organizations make strategic decisions and consider tradeoffs, and how communicating with other companies shaped long term success. This experience made me realize that I am looking to expand my skillset beyond just what I learn in my engineering curriculum to things like market research, data analysis of real companies, financial modeling, and thinking about the impact that startups/products have on the customers. The Financial Technology vertical is one that is exciting for me. I am currently conducting research in the School of Computing on large language models and the newest AI technologies. I am gaining a deeper understanding of modern AI systems, their capabilities, and emerging issues in these technologies such as privacy risks and deployment/training data tradeoffs. This research has pushed me to think beyond just the engineering and technical aspect of innovation in technology, but more about the impacts it can have on businesses. How do we choose what technologies are the best to be responsibly and effectively applied to help solve problems in sectors like healthcare and finance? 

Hillside’s focus, especially the Financial Innovation Vertical, would allow me to connect my technical background with making important investment decisions while learning more about software like Crunchbase, understanding financial numbers(burn rate, churn rate, and ROI), and becoming more well rounded for any field. What makes me most excited about this possible opportunity is the fact that Hillside is somewhere where I can learn these skills along like-minded peers across all different academic backgrounds as well as experienced professors from the School of Business. I see Hillside as a perfect learning opportunity and community that can help me contribute to the growth of startups, develop a deeper understanding of venture capital and how investors make decisions, and prepare me for a meaningful career which I enjoy!', contribution = 'Between my technical background that I have gained through my computer science coursework and personal data science projects/certifications and my previous internship experiences working for companies like The Hartford and Hartford HealthCare, I have gained a perfect mix of technical and communication skills that can help me succeed in this role. I am still improving on all of these areas, but my eagerness to learn more about the financial sector, specifically financial technologies that leverage AI/ML, will help me to be motivated as I learn new skills and face challenges in this role.

Zooming into my relevant technical experience, I have experience working with large datasets and analyzing them to identify trends and patterns, which is an important skill when evaluating potential startups to invest in. This skill set would allow me to meaningfully contribute to the due diligence and to bring a more technical mindset to the process of analyzing metrics and assessing whether a company''s data supports its growth and scalability claims. I can also add value by serving as a bridge between technical and business stakeholders/perspectives. My current research on LLMs, Agentic AI, and machine learning training has led me to develop a comprehensive understanding of how the newest technologies work behind the scenes and implementation, as well as awareness of their risks like privacy, tradeoffs post- deployment of models, and quality of training data. This can be valuable in the Financial Technology vertical, as I can help evaluate technology driven startups more realistically and assess if the technology product is worth investing in considering all its factors in AI/fintech.


In addition, my internship experience at Hartford HealthCare as an IT Project Management Intern strengthened my communication and teamwork skills, especially learning how to communicate effectively with both technical and business stakeholders, as well as managing teams with different priorities. I worked on many different projects in the healthcare space, and got to think in the lens of customers and users rather than just profit. I would be able to apply these skills during the process of due diligence and communicating with startup founders, doing market research, and having conversations where decisions and tradeoffs need to be considered. But most importantly, I am very excited about continuous growth and the possible opportunity to actively contribute to sourcing top startups in important areas and advancing my own self growth at the same time.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Ria Verma';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.5, major = 'Communications and Political Science', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/aaron-rouse-167b4422b/', why_hillside = 'As someone who wants to move into investor relations, sourcing deals and building/maintaining relationships with entrepreneurs directly mirrors the type of work IR teams do in the private equity space. I believe that being part of Hillside would be a powerful stepping stone for me because it blends analytical work with founder engagement. This is one of the few opportunities on campus where students can actively practice evaluating companies and articulating those insights in ways that have real_world impact. Through my conversations with individuals in the field, I’ve learned that this is exactly the type of foundation investor relations professionals rely on. I hope to build the judgment and relationship_management abilities that will shape my professional journey in the broader investment world.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a perspective that most traditional business_focused analysts don’t have. As a communications and political science major, I’m trained to think about how narratives land with the public and how messaging shapes market trust. These skills matter tremendously when evaluating a startup’s long_term viability. During the last information session, my initial instinct was to push back on Veracity because of concerns around its lack of branding and marketing, especially given the nuance of the GLP_1 space. I can offer a unique lens that helps assess whether companies can communicate effectively with their targeted consumers and the broader market. My experience working in marketing agencies has given me a strong background in evaluating whether a company’s positioning is compelling and credible. I’m confident that my experience and skills can help the fund make more holistic and well_rounded investment decisions.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Aaron Rouse';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.43, major = 'Management & Entrepreneurship', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/kaia-wotzak', why_hillside = 'I''m drawn to Hillside Ventures because of the unique opportunity to speak with founders, gain hands-on experience, and learn more about the CPG sector of venture capital.
 
