UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.3, major = 'Economics B.A.', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/riley-ramirez-539641298/', why_hillside = 'This is my second time applying for the Hillside Ventures Genesis Fund, and I couldn''t be more adamant about my excitement for the opportunity. I love the idea of being a member of Hillside Ventures because it gives you the opportunity to get hands on experience in investing, financial technology and working with other students who share the same desires as you. This to me is a perfect opportunity to learn from others who may be wiser than you are, improve your tangible skills and grow within the world of finance and investing.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis fund for several different reasons. The first being my ability to work well with others and get tasks done within a group. On my resume you see I have competed in and won multiple pitch competitions one for entrepreneurship over the summer and one this past semester in the Finance Society stock pitch. This reflects both my drive to learn and grow and also my ability to work with different groups in different fields and find success. Secondly, my overall experience has tremendous value. This coming summer I will be interning in a finance role in New York city. This opportunity will provide me with a ton of experience that will translate to my impact on Hillside Ventures. Lastly, just my overall involvement and hard work. Here at UConn, I am a member of several clubs, in which I am hoping to be on the executive board of soon and I work a part time job here on campus as well. I know I can be a smart, reliable and hardworking member who can achieve tasks and work well with any of my peers.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Riley Ramirez';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.83, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/evanespino333/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures appeals to me because it offers direct exposure to early-stage investing within a highly motivated, student-led environment. Through my experience in the Opportunity Fund, I’ve built a foundation in public markets, but I am still exploring which area of finance I ultimately want to pursue. Venture capital presents a different perspective! Valuating innovation at its earliest stages, understanding founder vision, and thinking long-term about value creation. Which is something I’m eager to learn more about.
I am also drawn to the culture Hillside represents. I want to be part of a team of hardworking, like-minded individuals who take investing seriously and push one another to improve. The opportunity to collaborate on sourcing, diligence, and portfolio growth is especially compelling. Contributing to and helping startups alongside a driven group of peers is exactly the kind of experience I am looking for.', contribution = 'I will contribute to the Genesis Fund through disciplined research, strong work ethic, and a commitment to team-oriented results. By next semester, through my continued involvement in the Opportunity Fund, I will have further developed my ability to analyze financial statements, evaluate risk, build investment theses, and clearly articulate and defend positions. I plan to bring that analytical foundation into Genesis Fund and apply it in a thoughtful and rigorous way.
Beyond that, I will contribute by being fully engaged and dependable. I will come to meetings prepared, ask thoughtful questions, and actively participate in discussions rather than sitting back. If something needs to be done. Whether it’s digging deeper into a company’s fundamentals or refining a pitch, I will take initiative and follow through. I want to be someone the team can rely on, not just for analysis, but for consistency and effort.
I will also bring a genuine desire to grow alongside the fund. I’m still figuring out exactly where I want to focus within finance, which motivates me to learn as much as possible and take feedback seriously. I will approach this opportunity with humility, curiosity, and a willingness to put in the extra work needed to improve. Not just for myself, but to help strengthen the team as a whole.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Evan Espino';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.7, major = 'Finance Major, Computer Science Minor', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/egor-vas/', why_hillside = 'I am interested in Hillside Ventures because it stands out to me as an organization at UConn which can let students have an actual impact on rising companies and founders. While most other finance organizations on campus focus on public equities and larger companies, Hillside Ventures stands at an intersection point between traditional finance and the innovation-focused startup field. As someone who chose to pursue a finance major but holds a deep interest in technology, innovation, and especially the current AI industry, Hillside seems like the perfect place to combine my interests and learn more about venture capital through hands-on work. Additionally, in the future I''d love to become a founder, and have already played around with the idea of a startup. The experience that I''d gain being part of this organization will only help further that vision, as well as being surrounded by likeminded, driven individuals with a sense of agency.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund in a variety of ways. I have experience being in organizations that require heavy involvement, namely the Finance Society and the Opportunity Fund. Through these experiences, I''ve grown to enjoy collaborative environments of students that have a mission. I''ll bring this mindset to Hillside Ventures, and I am excited to have the opportunity to work with other analysts on finding interesting and innovative startups.

Additionally, my experiences on campus (with finance-related organizations especially,) have taught me how to examine companies and understand their structure. Namely, the Opportunity Fund has been incredibly helpful in this regard, teaching me how to examine a companies financials, management, and be able to model realistic growth. While the Opportunity Fund focuses on public, mid-cap companies, the premise of being able to analyze a company is the same, with the only difference being scale and availability of data. I can bring this experience to the Genesis Fund and hit the ground running.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Egor Vasilyev';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.76, major = 'Economics/ Social Impact and Responsibility in Business', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/grejs-shelcaj-277081289', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures stands out to me because it successfully brings together investing, entrepreneurship, and real-world impact. As a UCONN student studying economics, I am deeply interested in how capital allocation can shape innovation and new opportunities. Hillside is a platform that helps its students think like investors, which means evaluating risk and also supporting a lot of early-stage ideas with real strategic insight. What especially draws me to Hillside is the focus on venture thinking, especially at the Undergraduate level. Venture capital requires someone to be analytical, yet curious about emerging industries. Additionally, it is important to have strong pattern recognition, which are skills i am actively developing through my coursework and independent learning. I want to better understand how founders are evaluated, how markets are assessed day to day, and how long-term value is something identified earlier on. I would be excited to be able to learn all these useful skills while also collaborating with other students. Venture investing is team-driven, and it requires perspective, conviction, and debate. Being surrounded by ambitious, forward-thinking peers would help me push into more challenging topics and sharpen my analysis while better communicating ideas. I am interested in Hillside Ventures because I don''t just want to study business theory, but I want to be exposed to the decision-making division, where capital meets innovation. Hillside is that bridge.', contribution = 'I can bring both a unique and practical perspective to the Genesis Fund. Having immigrated from Albania, I have developed resilience, adaptability, and a global perspective on opportunities. These qualities enable me to think creatively about global markets and unconventional business models. On the professional side, my experiences at UBS Wealth Management and my investment banking internship at Strong Capital Markets have provided me with hands-on exposure to financial analysis, market research, and evaluating investment opportunities. I have learned how to assess risk, perform due diligence, and also communicate complex financial concepts clearly. All of these are skills directly applicable to evaluating startups and making strategic investment decisions. 
Additionally, I bring a big interest in emerging industries and innovation, combined with a collaborative mindset. I enjoy working in teams to analyze opportunities, challenge assumptions, and also develop swift strategies. I am confident that traits of personal resilience, professional experience, and curiosity for high-growth ventures can contribute meaningfully to the Genesis Fund''s mission of identifying and supporting the next generation of impactful startups.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Grejs Shelcaj';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.6, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://linkedin.com/in/albi-bylyku', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures stands out to me because I love the idea of taking what we learn and actually applying it to real-world investments where our decisions truly matter. It’s one thing to study these topics, but it’s different when you’re working with real capital and real companies. That kind of hands-on experience is what really builds practical skills and confidence. I see Hillside as a place that will help me gain true experience that prepares me for my career long term.', contribution = 'I genuinely enjoy breaking down how a company works, how it makes money, what makes it stand out, and where it can grow. I like understanding the story behind the numbers and digging into the details which is something I get to do when directly interacting with the company founders as well. I can contribute by doing thorough research and helping the team see the full picture before making decisions. I’ll ask questions, stay engaged, and bring consistent effort.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Albi Bylyku';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Analytics Information Management', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/ethanmasoperh', why_hillside = 'As a pre-law student in the School of Business, I am always looking for opportunities that let me connect law and business in a practical way. Hillside Ventures immediately stood out to me because it offers exactly that experience. Working with startups and founders while evaluating investments provides exposure to both business decision making and the legal considerations that come with it. Venture capital is closely tied to legal work. Investing in companies involves understanding deal structures, contracts, and compliance. Portfolio management, for example, requires attention to governance, risk, and making sure companies operate within proper standards. Closing deals also requires careful consideration of terms and agreements. These are areas I want to better understand, especially since I am interested in pursuing a career that combines business, technology, and law. Many pre-law opportunities on campus focus on advocacy experiences like mock trial or debate. While those are valuable, my interests lean more toward transactional and strategic work. I want hands-on exposure to how legal and business decisions interact in real situations. Hillside Ventures, as a student-led venture capital fund at UConn, offers a unique way to gain that kind of experience. What especially attracts me is the perspective Hillside provides. It allows me to see how investors evaluate opportunities, assess risk, and work with founders. Understanding that viewpoint is important for anyone interested in business-related law. Overall, Hillside Ventures represents the type of experiential learning I am seeking. It would allow me to develop a stronger understanding of how legal principles shape real business decisions while gaining meaningful, hands-on experience.', contribution = 'I think I could contribute to the Genesis Fund by combining my analytical mindset, legal exposure, and ability to work well with people. Through my Yale ITS internship, I developed a strong comfort with analyzing data, identifying trends, and thinking critically about performance and efficiency. That experience strengthened how I approach problem solving and evaluating information, which I know is important when assessing companies and opportunities. Similarly, my involvement in case competitions and Case Club pushed me to think strategically, break down complex problems, and work closely with teams to reach clear decisions. My legal internship at Trachten Law Firm added another layer to how I think. Being exposed to property closings, zoning matters, and real transactions helped me better understand structure, risk, and the importance of detail-oriented decision making. It gave me a practical perspective on how deals and agreements actually work, which connects naturally to venture investing. Beyond my experiences, one of my biggest strengths is that I am very sociable and genuinely enjoy working with others. I’m comfortable engaging in discussions, building relationships, and collaborating in team environments. I like being someone who actively contributes ideas and energy rather than just observing. Overall, I would bring strong analytical thinking, thoughtful decision making, and a collaborative presence to the Genesis Fund.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Ethan Masoperh';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.98, major = 'Analytics and Information Management', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/davidkang-hk/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures stands out to me because it aligns with how I learn best. I grow the most when I am researching, asking questions, and learning through real work with motivated people. I am naturally curious, and I enjoy the process of turning that curiosity into a clearer understanding of how a business works and why it can grow.

I recently joined the Opportunity Fund, and even in a short time, it has helped me build more disciplined research habits and strengthen my interest in investing. That experience is still new for me, but it made me want to keep improving in an environment where I can learn by doing and get feedback from others.

What also drew me to Hillside was a conversation I had with one of the members. What stood out was how they described the group''s learning process. They explained how someone who starts with limited knowledge of investing, especially startup investing, can become more capable through hands-on work, experience, and guidance from the team. That kind of growth-oriented environment is exactly what I am looking for.

My internship experience at a Korean venture capital firm also widened the way I see companies and startups. I was exposed to new technologies, new ideas, and founders who were deeply driven by what they were building. Being around that kind of energy made me more interested in the broader business world and in the thinking behind how companies grow.

I am especially interested in Hillside because of its different sectors and verticals. I currently do independent research in tech and shipping stocks, but I want to broaden my perspective and learn from members focused on other industries. I believe Hillside Ventures would help me grow as a researcher, teammate, and future finance professional.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund because I care about being useful in the actual work, not just being around it. I like the process of figuring things out. When a company or market is unclear at first, I enjoy digging into it, organizing the information, and turning it into something the team can actually use in discussion. That kind of work fits me well, and I know it matters in a fund environment.

I would bring consistency and strong follow-through. I am also the type of person who prepares carefully, pays attention to details, and takes responsibility for doing things properly. If there is research to do, founder call preparation, market mapping, or support work for diligence, I am ready to take it seriously and improve through feedback. I do not want to be involved only at the surface level. I want to help the fund run better by doing the work that makes decision-making stronger.

I also bring a perspective shaped by living and studying in different countries and environments. When looking at a firm or a product, I constantly think about how customer behavior, market conditions, and growth strategies can look very different depending on the country or setting. Furthermore, when looking at startups, I tend to think not only about whether an idea is good, but also where it works best and what might need to change for it to grow elsewhere. I think my way of thinking can add value when evaluating opportunities.

What stands out most about me is that I genuinely love learning. I am applying to Genesis Fund because I want to build real judgment, work with people who take investing seriously, and grow by contributing in a hands-on way. I would bring curiosity and discipline every time the team needs someone to step up.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Hyeongyu Kang (Preferred Name: David)';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/kiril-kovalenko/', why_hillside = 'I want to join Hillside Ventures because it offers real experience in venture capital, not just classroom learning. Students have the opportunity to find startups, research them carefully, and help decide how to invest real money. I believe this kind of hands-on experience is the best way to truly understand finance. As a passionate and motivated student, I am always looking for opportunities that challenge me and help me grow. Hillside would allow me to apply what I learn in class to real companies and real decisions.

I am especially interested in fintech. I am very curious about how technology is changing the financial industry. Fintech combines finance and innovation, which makes it exciting and fast-growing. Through Hillside’s focus on Financial Innovation, I would be able to analyze fintech startups, understand their business models, and learn how they create value. This would help me build strong knowledge in an area of finance that I care deeply about.

I am also excited about the investment process at Hillside. Sourcing deals and conducting due diligence requires attention to detail, critical thinking, and teamwork. I enjoy researching companies, asking questions, and looking deeper into how a business works. I believe being part of a diligence group would help me improve my analytical skills and become more confident in evaluating investment opportunities.

I value Hillside’s mission to create opportunities for students from different backgrounds and to prepare the next generation of professionals. As someone who moved to the United States recently, I understand how important it is to have supportive communities that encourage growth and ambition. I am a hardworking and dedicated student, and I would bring strong commitment, curiosity, and a willingness to learn to Hillside Ventures. I see this not only as a learning opportunity, but also as a chance to contribute to a team of driven students who are serious about building careers in finance.

I believe Hillside Ventures would push me to grow both professionally and personally. Working with other motivated students and experienced mentors would challenge me to think more deeply and communicate my ideas clearly. I am not afraid of hard work, and I am always willing to put in extra time to fully understand a concept or complete a task well. As a passionate student who truly cares about building a strong future in finance, I would take this opportunity very seriously. I am eager to contribute, learn from others, and help Hillside continue to succeed.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing strong dedication, curiosity, and a serious commitment to learning. I am a very passionate student who truly cares about building a future in finance. When I join an organization, I give it my full effort and attention. I am not afraid of difficult work, and I am willing to spend extra time researching, analyzing, and improving my skills. I understand that managing real capital is a serious responsibility, and I would approach every task with professionalism and focus.

Through my involvement in the Opportunity Fund Project, I have been developing important investment skills. In this program, our professor teaches us how to properly analyze companies, read financial statements, evaluate business models, and understand risk. We learn how to think critically before making investment decisions. Next semester, I will be managing a fund together with my team, where we will make real investment decisions. This experience is teaching me accountability, teamwork, and how to make thoughtful, data-driven decisions, skills that directly apply to the Genesis Fund.

I am especially interested in fintech and Financial Innovation, which aligns strongly with one of the Genesis Fund’s focus areas. I am very curious about how technology is changing banking, investing, and payments. I enjoy learning about new financial platforms, digital assets, and emerging technologies. Because of this interest, I would be highly motivated to research fintech startups deeply, understand their revenue models, analyze risks, and evaluate their long-term growth potential. My genuine interest would push me to go beyond basic analysis and look at the bigger picture.

In addition, I have strong research habits and attention to detail. When evaluating a company, I would carefully study its market size, competition, leadership team, and financial projections. I understand that early-stage investing requires critical thinking and careful due diligence. I would take sourcing seriously by actively looking for promising startups, especially those connected to UConn alumni or within the Genesis Fund’s target industries. I would be proactive rather than waiting for opportunities to come to me.

I also believe I can contribute positively to the team environment. I respect different opinions and enjoy discussing ideas with others. Venture investing requires collaboration, and strong investment decisions come from thoughtful debate. I would listen carefully to my peers, contribute my ideas clearly, and remain open to feedback. I believe that healthy discussion leads to better outcomes, and I would aim to be both confident and humble in group settings.

As someone who moved to the United States not long ago, I bring a unique perspective and resilience. Adjusting to a new country and academic system has strengthened my discipline and determination. I do not take opportunities for granted. Being part of the Genesis Fund would mean a lot to me, and I would show that through consistent effort and reliability. I understand that trust is important when working with real capital, and I would work hard to earn that trust.

I am deeply motivated to build a long-term career in finance, and I see the Genesis Fund as an opportunity to grow both academically and professionally. I want to develop strong analytical skills, improve my understanding of venture capital, and learn from experienced mentors. At the same time, I want to contribute meaningful work and help the fund make smart investment decisions. My passion, dedication, and strong work ethic would allow me to add value to the Genesis Fund while continuing to grow as a future finance professional.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Kiril Kovalenko';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.79, major = 'Analysis and Information Management', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jiaying-lyu-3175293b3?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Ad_flagship3_profile_view_base_contact_details%3BIX3X2pFHTsyY6MRDiMQBsQ%3D%3D', why_hillside = 'I want to join Hillside Ventures because I want to move beyond the screen and understand the core of business building. My experience in US equity trading taught me a lot about risk and market sentiment, but it’s limited to secondary market data. I want to learn the fundamentals of venture capital—how to evaluate a team, a product, and a business model before it even reaches the public market. I’m looking for a professional environment where I can start as a Student Analyst, learn the rigorous due diligence process, and contribute to the most serious investment team at UConn.', contribution = 'I can contribute by handling the more data-intensive and technical aspects of research that early-stage funds often require. My background in Physics and Robotics means I’m not intimidated by complex technical whitepapers; I can help the team parse through these details and summarize the core logic. Also, being Bloomberg certified, I can immediately take over the ''legwork'' of market screening and data pulling. I’m ready to do the ground-level research and use my technical literacy to make the team’s due diligence process more efficient from day one.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Jiaying Lyu';
