UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.3, major = 'Mechanical Engineering', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/caroline-bernacki/', why_hillside = 'I’m interested in Hillside Ventures because it offers a unique opportunity to gain hands-on experience evaluating startups and making real investment decisions as a college student. I’m excited to expand beyond technical coursework and learn how new technologies are assessed and brought to life. This experience would allow me to better understand the world of entrepreneurship and innovation, something I hope to pursue further.', contribution = 'As a mechanical engineering student, I bring a technical perspective that allows me to evaluate the feasibility of various technologies and ideas. Throughout high school, I served as the vice-president of the Environmental Action Committee, where I led sustainability initiatives and developed a strong interest in creating a zero waste world; an experience that has driven me to apply for the sustainability vertical of Hillside Ventures.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Caroline Bernacki';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 2.99, major = 'Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/zion-joseph', why_hillside = 'I am interested in Hillside ventures because it is a way for me to contribute on campus. This opportunity is one that I will not take for granted if given the opportunity because I can see this helping me in areas other than venture capital. Hillside ventures will help me develop relationships with other people with the same interest as me and will also help me make connections with professionals in the financial industry. One of the main reasons I chose Hillside over any other club is because Hillside takes time to do research on a company by meeting with the founders to see what goals they would like to accomplish and help the company grow. Another reason that I am applying is to gain hands on experience, and Hillside offers just that. Hillside is a place where it is set up for everyone to succeed in gaining knowledge to improve their investment skills. What also caught my interest is the teamwork environment that hillside has where everyone is genuinely happy to see everyone win and hopes for the best for everyone in the environment. There are many reasons to join Hillside, but these are the reasons why I am interested.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the genesis fund by bringing in analytical thinking, interest, and passion toward the fund. Even though I lack experience, I am a fast learner who will be glad to acquire the abilities needed to become a productive team member who can contribute meaningfully to the work. I think that my readiness to learn, adapt, and take initiative would enable me to learn the investment strategy and portfolio focus of the Fund quickly. Fin tech is a specific interest of mine because it is changing the way people and companies access capital, risk, and create wealth. The emergence of AI-based financial tools and digital payments is changing traditional financial systems and creating more inclusive and effective ones. Joining the fund would give me an opportunity to experience and invest in this innovation. I would be helpful in assisting research on new fintech ventures, market research, and aiding in assessing expansion opportunities. I am also extremely encouraged to ask questions, receive feedback, and improve whatever is needed. I am a dedicated person with a strong work ethic which I believe would help me gain the necessary expertise to contribute significantly towards the Genesis Fund mission.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Zion Joseph';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.94, major = 'Computer Science and Engineering', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/julia-tkachuk-kyrychenko', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures is an environment that pushes individuals to grow by expanding their skill set. While my classes give me the technical foundation; understanding financial statements, valuation concepts, and market theory, they don’t fully replicate the process of sourcing deals, conducting due diligence, and defending an investment thesis in a real-world setting. Being part of Hillside Ventures would allow me to bridge that gap.

The ability to look at a company and perform an in-depth analysis from a surface-level view is a skill I want to develop. In Hillside, I would learn how to navigate ambiguity, how to ask the right questions, assess qualitative factors like management and market positioning, and think critically about risk in ways that aren’t always taught in lectures.

The process of identifying a company that seems like an interesting investment and then digging into its fundamentals and financial logistics is not only applicable to venture capital, but across finance especially equity research, which I’m particularly interested in. As someone who learns best through hands-on experience and direct application, Hillside Ventures would push me to move beyond theory and actively apply what I know, while also teaching me the practical, judgment-based skills that can only be developed through real investment work.', contribution = 'My ability to approach projects with an open mind, strong desire to learn, and genuine curiosity would allow me to both grow within and meaningfully contribute to Hillside Ventures. I want to join because it is a space where thoughtful analysis and intellectual curiosity directly translate into real investment decisions, and I am eager to be in an environment where my mindset can add value to a team while sharpening my own skills.

As a student, I operate under the assumption that there is something to learn from everything and that differing perspectives are not obstacles but advantages. In Hillside, this would allow me to contribute to productive discussions, challenge assumptions respectfully, and remain receptive to feedback when refining an investment thesis. An open mind would also push me to seriously evaluate companies within my vertical that may initially seem less compelling, ensuring opportunities are not overlooked simply because they fall outside of obvious trends.

My curiosity strengthens this further. I naturally question details, including market dynamics, competitive positioning, financial drivers, and management decisions, because I want to understand not just what is happening but why. When analyzing a company, I would explore multiple angles, connect insights across industries, and dig into both qualitative and quantitative factors to form a well-rounded perspective.

Ultimately, my curiosity and openness make me an exploratory thinker, someone willing to dive deeper, challenge surface-level conclusions, and continuously improve. That mindset is exactly why I want to join Hillside Ventures and how I would contribute.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Julia Tkachuk-Kyrychenko';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.75, major = 'Major:Economics, Minor:Statistics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/nick-taipe', why_hillside = 'As a rising Economics Sophomore, i desire growth, and to learn more by hands on experiences. Im eager to apply my curiosity and fascination towards real world investment decisions, and once i heard information talks from representatives encouraging us ambitious students to apply, i knew it was my calling. As a Economics major i''ve been learning how the market functions, what factors drive changes, and how data can be used to make better informed decision making which is what an individual with curiosity and eagerness to learn must know. What caught my attention is that members of this organization are overseen and mentored along the way, and are also given that exposure to venture investing. With over a $1 million dollar venture capital fund that is used and by their students to invest in startups, and that says a lot about the trust and reliability an individual must have to be a part of hillside ventures. As a Freshman, i bring strong willingness to learn, unwavering work ethic, and genuine passion for finance. Im excited and honored to be able to even apply for a opportunity like this and have the chance to contribute, and grow with within the venture capital realm alongside with ambitious and passion driven peers just like myself.', contribution = 'I believe i can contribute to the Genesis Fund at Hillside Ventures greatly by my strong attention to detail and a fresh point of view. Im excited to be able to speak up and engage in the weekly meetings held, support research in any way i can to the best of my efforts, and help discover upcoming trends that can be foreseen in the near future. As someone who wants to develop and learn, i''m interested on how these early stage companies grow early on and what makes them unique compared to others to set themselves apart from the competition. Learning about this opportunity during Finance society, i''m more then ever motivated to work and learn and see what kind of investor/person i can become from being part of a nurturing environment. To be able to contribute towards the team and be able to develop the critical skills on how to discover promising startups undoubtedly sounds like the best way for an investor to grow, leave a their mark within the fund, and be surrounded with peers who share the same passion for finance.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Nick Taipe';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.3, major = 'Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/almari-castillo', why_hillside = 'I am interested in Hillside Ventures because it blends two business and legal structures. As an accounting student, I am also interested in pre-law. Accounting has taught me how to read a company, but I have always wanted to go deeper than the financials. I want to develop a deep understanding of what builds a company, not just how to measure it once it exists, but also the strategy, risk, and judgment that go into creating it from the start. My long-term goal is law school, with a focus on corporate or transactional law, and my pre-law minor has given me a foundation to build on. But I want to be the kind of attorney who genuinely understands the business context behind the documents. Hillside Ventures gives me the real-world exposure to founder relationships and investment decisions that will make me a more credible and effective legal professional.', contribution = 'My experience in venture capital is still developing, but what I bring is a solid academic foundation, a curious mind, and a genuine commitment to learning everything this space has to offer and a set of concrete skills I have already put to work in real financial settings.

Earlier this year I earned my Bloomberg Finance Fundamentals Certificate, completing a comprehensive program covering economic money flow, investment strategies, and risk management. Around the same time, I became an IRS-certified VITA volunteer, preparing federal and state tax returns for low-to-moderate income individuals and families in my community. That experience taught me something I did not fully expect: that working directly with real financial situations is a kind of practical finance that cannot be replicated. I learned to ask the right questions and explain complex information clearly to people who were counting on me to get it right.

My accounting background gives me the ability to look at a company''s numbers critically and identify where things do not add up. Combined with a strong sense of compliance and attention to detail, I believe I can add real value at the early stage of a company''s growth.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Almari Castillo';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.46, major = 'Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/aryakpatel', why_hillside = 'I view venture capital as an investment in the future. While not every startup will succeed, giving founders the capital and conviction to pursue their vision is meaningful in itself. That is what draws me to Hillside Ventures. Hillside stands out not only for its reputation but for its culture of accountability and collaboration. During my conversations in coffee chats, I consistently heard about analysts challenging one another, supporting one another, and holding each other to a higher standard. I want to be immersed in an environment where driven individuals push each other to think critically and perform at a higher level. The responsibility of evaluating companies and allocating capital carries real consequences for founders who have committed their time and careers to building something impactful. That responsibility demands rigor, discipline, and respect. Hillside offers exposure that cannot be replicated in a classroom, from engaging directly with founders and alumni to analyzing live investment opportunities and seeing the results of those decisions. I am ambitious and intentional about where I invest my energy, and Hillside represents a community where I can contribute meaningfully while being challenged to grow.', contribution = 'I would contribute to the Genesis Fund through discipline, accountability, and a strong balance of analytical rigor and interpersonal awareness. When I set a goal, I commit fully and follow through with consistency. My coursework in managerial accounting and financial management has strengthened my ability to interpret financial statements beyond the surface level and focus on what truly drives performance, risk, and long term sustainability. I have learned that the numbers only matter if you understand what they represent and why they matter. At the same time, my 