UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.94, major = 'Major in Finance, minor in Statistics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexander-greenberg-', why_hillside = 'I am extremely interested in joining the Hillside Ventures Genesis Fund team because it is an opportunity to gain experience managing actual capital and sourcing real deals. It is an opportunity to learn in an environment where my choices have genuine consequences instead of simulated ones and receive mentorship from professors with decades of experience in the industry. This not only will help me excel within the school of business but also help prepare me for a career in highly competitive industries. Furthermore, the investment thesis directly resonates with me. Specifically, I am excited about the Sustainability vertical. Coming from a beach community, I have always been interested in how businesses can provide sustainable solutions to environmental and economic crisis''s that threaten our local marine ecosystems. This is a direct example of Hillside Ventures definition of sustainability startups that we would invest in.', contribution = 'I will contribute to the Genesis Fund by being a productive, hardworking member. I am able to effectively balance time, allowing me to be an active member of the fund and dedicate ample time to sourcing deals and researching possible startups. I am eager to learn, create new connections, and lead in an industry that I am actively pursuing a career in. With each meeting of Finance Society or Investment Banking Society, I gain knew knowledge that I can apply to my research for the fund. I also stay up to date on current events, both social and political, which can have significant implications on the fund''s portfolio. Furthermore, I have personal interests and experience in each of the verticals. With Sports and Wellness, I have been an athlete for most of my life, a referee for almost 8 years, and a ski instructor for the past 4 winters. Due to this, I am able to understand whether a startup would solve a real problem. With sustainability, I have experience in environmental work and environmental crises, and a genuine interest in promoting sustainability and conservation. With financial innovation, I am constantly building my knowledge in market structure, valuations, and how math and models can create change in the industry. Finally, with Consumer Products, while a newer topic to me, I am becoming more experienced in how technology amplifies the human learning experience', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Alexander Greenberg';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/kaelyn-horn-4373bb335', why_hillside = 'I am interested in joining Hillside Ventures because it offers a rare opportunity to gain hands-on venture capital experience while still in college. I am excited by the opportunity to evaluate real startup companies, conduct due diligence, and contribute to meaningful investment decisions. Hillside stands out to me because it is not just a club, but a student-led investment fund where members collaborate to source, analyze, and invest in early-stage companies. Gaining hands-on experience is essential for truly understanding venture capital, as applying concepts in real investment situations develops skills and judgment that cannot be fully learned in a classroom setting. 

I am especially drawn to venture capital because it combines finance, strategy, innovation, and entrepreneurship. Unlike traditional investing, venture capital focuses on early-stage companies where growth potential, scalability, and market opportunity are critical factors. I find it exciting to research startups, analyze their competitive positioning, and assess whether they have the potential to grow. Venture capital also allows investors to stay engaged with emerging industries and evolving market trends. 

Hillside offers an opportunity to develop skills in market analysis, competitive positioning, and risk assessment while working alongside a driven, collaborative team. I also value the opportunity to learn from experienced mentors, as guidance from those with industry knowledge is crucial in developing strong investment judgment and understanding how venture capital decisions are made. Being a part of Hillside would allow me to apply concepts from my business coursework to real investment decisions, gain mentorship from experienced leaders, and deepen my understanding of the early-stage investment landscape.', contribution = 'I would be a strong, contributing member of the Hillside Venture Genesis Fund. Through multiple leadership roles, including Vice President of Education for my sorority and Secretary of the Honors in Business Association, I have developed a solid foundation in leadership, collaboration, and effective team management. These experiences have strengthened my interpersonal skills, multitasking ability, critical thinking, and attention to detail. Additionally, I can contribute by analyzing potential investment opportunities using knowledge gained from my coursework in financial management and marketing, to help evaluate business models, growth potential, and marketing positioning. 

In my previous role at The Village Coffee Bar, I gained firsthand exposure to the operational challenges small businesses face, including managing costs, driving customer retention, and operating efficiently in a fast-paced, ever-changing environment. This experience strengthened my understanding of unit economics and the realities early-stage companies encounter, which I can apply when assessing potential investments. 

Ultimately, I believe I would be a valuable asset to the Genesis Fund. I am not only eager to gain hands-on experience in venture capital but am also motivated to dedicate myself fully to supporting the fund’s mission. With my interest in sports and wellness, I can identify promising early-stage companies in the space, conduct thorough research, assess risk factors, and contribute meaningful, data-driven insights within a collaborative team environment. I bring a strong work ethic and ensure that my contributions will be supported by thoughtful analysis and preparation.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Kaelyn Horn';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.6, major = 'Analytics & Information Management Major and Political Science Minor', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/nikitapanwar124', why_hillside = 'I want to be a part of Hillside Ventures because I think analyzing early-stage businesses to gauge if they could be successful is a skill that is transferable to almost any field and creates a systematic way of thinking that is applicable throughout your career. Personally, I find researching through different buisness''s charcteristics and patterns to recognize their potential to be interesting and genuinely enganging which is why I aim to be a part of Hillside Ventures.', contribution = 'I have a background of leadership in a wide array of organizations throughout high school, such as debate, DECA, cross country, and a non-profit organization, and all of these experiences have taught me how to approach problems from multiple angles, which I could contribute to the Genesis Fund. Specifically in the financial technology vertical, I would be able to contribute my background in the cross-space between technology and business. I enjoyed studying and taking on projects within that space, which has made me well-versed in AI and AI usage in corporations.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Nikita Panwar';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.87, major = 'Major: Physiology and Neurobiology Minor: Bioinformatics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2027', linkedin_url = 'https://linkedin.com/in/faryal-akbar', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures feels like the natural next step for me because it sits exactly where my experiences with startups, research, and campus sustainability intersect. Through the Office of Sustainability, I’ve already been on the front lines of thinking about how external companies can plug into UConn’s operations, Whether that’s exploring partners for more sustainable lab PPE practices or working with other startups to reduce campus energy waste, I’ve been directly involved in seeing how sustainability_focused startups can integrate into UConn’s operations. That work has pushed me to think beyond “Is this a good sustainability idea?” toward questions about stakeholders, adoption, and long_term viability, which aligns closely with how an early_stage investor has to think. 

At the same time, I’ve spent the last year getting a very direct view inside early_stage companies. Over the summer, I worked with startups through the Technology Incubation Program, seeing how founders prioritize limited time and resources, respond to feedback, and iterate on both product and story. Now, I’m doing research for a biotech startup developing a microneedle bandage for chronic, infected wounds, which has me deep in the science but also constantly aware that every experiment ultimately feeds into questions about differentiation, regulatory strategy, and clinical need. Hillside gives me the chance to bring those perspectives into a more structured investing environment, connecting what I see in the lab and in OS to how a fund evaluates risk, traction, and market opportunity. 

I’m drawn to Hillside specifically because it’s student_run and expects analysts to do real work: sourcing, building simple but thoughtful analyses, and debating investment theses as a team. I want to learn how to look at a startup not just as a scientist or a sustainability intern, but as someone asking: Is this the right team, solving the right problem, in a way that can scale? Hillside’s mix of STEM_driven investing, exposure to founders, and a collaborative culture makes it the ideal place for me to grow that mindset while contributing to my experience working with startups and sustainability initiatives on and around campus.', contribution = 'I can contribute three main things to the Hillside Genesis Fund: domain insight in healthcare and biotech, real startup and sustainability experience, and a rigorous, research_driven mindset. 

First, my background in biotech and healthcare means I’m comfortable in regulated, science_heavy environments. I’ve worked closely with a biotech startup developing microneedle bandages for chronic, infected wounds, which has meant thinking about pathogens, experimental design, and ultimately how something gets from bench science toward real patients. That experience would help Hillside when looking at companies in digital health, life_science tools, or climate/health intersections.

Second, I’ve already spent time inside early_stage teams through both the Technology Incubation Program and the Office of Sustainability. Being around scrappy biotech founders and working on campus-facing sustainability projects has shown me how small teams prioritize, iterate, and talk to customers and stakeholders. I’ve seen the gap between a polished pitch and what it takes to execute, which I think is useful when evaluating whether a founding team truly understands its problem, has traction beyond slideware, and can deliver on health or climate impact rather than just describe it. 

Finally, I bring a very data_driven, collaborative approach from research and leadership roles on campus. I’m used to digging into primary sources, structuring messy information, and then communicating it clearly to non_experts. In Genesis, I would apply that to sourcing and screening deals, building simple but thoughtful analyses, and contributing actively to team discussions. I’m not coming in as a traditional finance major, but I think I can add value by bringing deep comfort with technical, regulated industries, hands_on experience inside early_stage biotech and sustainability efforts, and the willingness to learn the valuation and modeling side so I can help the team connect strong science and sustainability stories to real, investable business cases.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Faryal Akbar';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.5, major = 'Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/sebastian-ramos1', why_hillside = 'In order to answer, “why hillside ventures,” I think it’d be most appropriate to start from my freshman year when my knowledge of finance and venture capital was a bit more limited than it is now. People who I consider mentors such as Miles Dubois and Aime Mulungula acclimated me to the best opportunities on campus, with Hillside Ventures easily being at the top of the list. From there, I emphasized gaining base level knowledge of finance, while strengthening my resume and GPA throughout my freshman year. Fast-forward now, through going to info sessions and multiple coffee chats, I found my “why Hillside.” The possibility of real-world venture capital experience during undergraduate years (something not many institutions nationally possess) is the main factor as to why I’m interested in joining. Rather than simply learning these concepts in class, I’d be able to experientially learn through sourcing startups, conducting due diligence, engaging in market research, and networking with (as well as analyzing) founders. These experiences will allow me to strengthen the people and technical skills that are essential to thrive in finance. Even beyond skill development, getting to know the recruiters and analysts within the fund was engaging and rewarding. Through my coffee chats with current analysts, I found the competitive yet encouraging culture to be an environment that I can thrive in; where although everyone works together as a team, getting a deal through is the main goal for every vertical.', contribution = 'I believe that the strongest quality I can contribute to the genesis fund is my leadership and ability to collaborate. These two qualities are things I’d say I''ve worked on through my experience working with Scholars Learning Community as Vice President and floor mentor. Although my experience isn’t directly in finance, the skills I’ve worked on in that position certainly helped me in being able to work on a team for a common goal. For example, in my role I’m often tasked with planning and administering community events that take coordination with a group of people where I’ve learned how to identify when I need to take a lead or a back seat in a project. I see this to be essential in leadership as it shows adaptability and makes someone easier to work with. Within the Genesis Fund, I believe I would bring that same balance of initiative and humility that I’ve learned. I’m comfortable stepping up when leadership is needed, but I also value listening and learning from others which is essential in the classroom setting of Hillside.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Sebastian Ramos';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.5, major = 'Mechanical Engineering with Concentration in Energy and Power', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/justinaarongomes/', why_hillside = 'I first came across Hillside Ventures on Instagram a while ago, and what immediately caught my attention was that it manages real money. That honestly surprised me. It was not just a discussion based club or something purely theoretical. There is real responsibility behind it, and that made me curious. I made sure to check it out at the involvement fair, and after speaking with members there, I attended the info sessions. The more I learned, the more I wanted to be part of it.

    As a Mechanical Engineering student, most of my academic experience revolves around analytical thinking. I am used to breaking down problems, evaluating systems, and asking why something works the way it does. I do not have a formal finance background, but I am very comfortable with numbers and logical reasoning. What stood out to me during the sessions was how welcoming everything felt. It did not feel like you had to already know venture capital to belong. Concepts were explained clearly and questions were encouraged, which made it feel like a place where I can learn a lot.

    I have had coffee chats with Evan Courtney, Sai Patel, and Jacob Dooley, and those conversations really deepened my interest. One thing that stuck with me was learning how important it is to research not just the company itself, but also its investors. The type of capital backing a company can influence its direction, credibility, and long term trajectory. That perspective genuinely changed how I analyze companies, even in the personal trading I have been involved in since high school. I now will start to pay closer attention to investor alignment and capital signaling because it shapes outcomes more than I previously realized.

    Talking about companies like Climate Candy and DexMat also shifted my mindset. At first, I underestimated Climate Candy, but learning the reasoning behind the investment showed me how much deeper analysis goes beyond surface impressions. The DexMat discussion stood out to me as well. As someone concentrating in energy, the technology fascinated me. However, understanding why the deal ultimately did not move forward showed me that strong engineering alone is not enough. Market validation and investor confidence are just as critical. It shocked me how it even through it was partnered with NASA and other big companies, it still got rejected. I learned one reason was because no prior big time investor had invested in it which was shocking to me as well. What I took from this was I would be able to learn big time about emerging companies that pertain to what I am currently studying and I can make investment calls from actually understanding products in depth. Being able to be on the other side of engineering is really fascinating to me since it would help me be a better engineer in addition to the fact that I would like to pivot to the financial engineering side after a few years.

    What excites me most about Hillside, especially within the sustainability vertical, is how naturally it connects to my interests. I am deeply interested in renewable energy and emerging technologies, and I also genuinely enjoy following markets and understanding how capital flows. Being able to combine my engineering mindset with financial evaluation feels like a natural fit. It connects my education to my passion. 

    More than anything, I am drawn to the environment. I want to be surrounded by people who challenge each other, ask better questions, and push ideas further. Hillside feels like a place where I can grow, contribute from my engineering perspective, and continue developing both analytically and professionally. Overall I feel like can learn very essential information in a environment I feel happy to be in.', contribution = 'I think I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a perspective that blends engineering thinking with a genuine interest in markets and investing. As a Mechanical Engineering student concentrating in energy, I am used to thinking through problems step by step. Engineering has trained me to ask whether something actually works in practice, not just in theory. I naturally think about constraints, efficiency, scalability, and whether a solution is realistic beyond the initial idea. I believe that mindset can add value when evaluating early stage companies, especially those with technical products.

    My interest in finance started in high school when I began trading during the early cannabis legalization period. That experience made me curious about how markets work, how things influence capital, and how risk should be managed. Since then, I have continued following and investing in companies like Palantir and Nvidia early on, which pushed me to look beyond hype and focus more on long term positioning and if something has a solution to a problem that is needed. Through my coffee chats with Hillside members, I learned how important it is to research not only the company itself, but also its investors. Understanding who is backing a company and why can say a lot about its potential direction and credibility. That perspective taught me to evaluate opportunities differently.

    If selected for the sustainability vertical, I believe my academic focus in energy would allow me to contribute in a meaningful way. I built a solar powered Mars rover prototype and analyzed its efficiency, which deepened my interest in renewable technologies and performance tradeoffs. I am genuinely interested in climate tech and emerging energy systems, and I want to be able to distinguish between technology that is truly innovative and scalable versus technology that is simply well presented. Coming from an engineering background, I can evaluate whether something makes sense technically while also thinking about how it could succeed commercially.

    Beyond my technical background, I bring initiative and discipline. Engineering taught me quickly that if you fall behind, things pile up fast. I had to develop strong time management and take responsibility early instead of waiting until the last minute. That mindset carries into how I approach opportunities like Hillside. I scheduled multiple coffee chats, came prepared with questions, and took the time to understand the structure of the fund because I genuinely wanted to learn.

    Most importantly, I am very open to growth. I enjoy being challenged and learning from people who think differently than I do. I do not expect to know everything walking in. I want to absorb as much as possible, contribute thoughtfully to discussions, and help strengthen the analysis within my vertical. I believe my engineering mindset combined with my long standing interest in markets would allow me to add a unique and valuable perspective to the Genesis Fund.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Justin A. Gomes';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.4, major = 'Economics', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/malin-kiman-4b2358337/', why_hillside = 'I’m interested in finance long term with an aspiring career in asset management, especially investing and capital allocation, and Hillside is one of the few places on campus where students actually get to think like investors instead of just learning theory. As a current investor in my own accounts with Fidelity and Robinhood, being around people who take markets and venture seriously would push me to think at a higher level.', contribution = 'I bring a genuine interest in markets and growth companies. I actively follow trends in tech, AI, and financial innovation, and I enjoy breaking down business models and revenue drivers within the market and economy. Through my role in Student Activities Banking Services, Healthcare Assistant. I’ve developed a strong attention to detail around financial processes. I’m comfortable asking hard questions, using all my resources,  and putting in the work needed to understand a company deeply before forming an opinion.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Malin Kimani Gitau';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.6, major = 'Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/luke-sosnow-18ba9a334/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures stands out to me because it represents a unique intersection of student initiative and venture capital. Hillside provides an unparalleled opportunity to move beyond coursework and actively participate in sourcing and evaluating startups. I am particularly drawn to the Genesis Fund because it encourages investment decisions while fostering entrepreneurship within the broader UConn community. The exposure to due diligence, market research, financial modeling, and founder evaluation aligns closely with my academic interests in business and finance and my long-term goal of working in investment-oriented environments. What excites me most is the collaborative, results-oriented culture Hillside cultivates, working alongside driven peers to analyze real companies.', contribution = 'I believe I can contribute to the Genesis Fund through a strong work ethic and curiosity about early-stage business models. My background in accounting and finance coursework has strengthened my ability to break down financial statements, assess cost structures, and evaluate scalability, which are critical in venture investing. Beyond technical ability, I strive to be consistent and a strong leader. Being vice president of my fraternity and a captain of my high school tennis team, I am someone who prepares thoroughly, asks thoughtful questions, and actively engages in team-based environments. I would contribute not only through financial analysis but also by helping identify promising founders. I see Hillside Ventures not just as a learning opportunity, but as a platform where I can add real value while growing into a more strategic and responsible person.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Lucas Sosnow';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.75, major = 'Finance/Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/aditya-pnair', why_hillside = 'Out of all the funds at UConn, Hillside VC stood out to me the most for its reputation of giving students hands-on experience with real deals with a real budget. A brand I didn''t know came from the Hillside portfolio is "PlantBaby." It''s great to see this product is on shelves in actual stores; It showed me that the work done here is genuinely valuable and important to the world even outside of UConn. Hillside''s "vertical" system also drew me in as it means that the work I would do would be a topic in which I was heavily invested in; which I''d say is one of the most important things when looking for companies to pitch to peers. I aimed to be more invested in campus clubs and I believe this student fund is not only invaluable experience to have on a resume but also important to get comfortable with collaboration and critique culture in preparation for an analyst profession.', contribution = 'As a Finance major and aspiring Financial Analyst, I see Hillside VC as the next step from financial simulations to real-world experience. I''m eager to contribute by working with a team of people with diverse ideas in which I could focus my efforts on financial modeling, valuation and due diligence, helping the team assess the potential of early-stage companies. Other than numbers, I have a genuine curiosity for finding these ''diamond in the rough'' type companies through market research, which would support investment decisions and portfolio solidity. By working hands-on with deals I aim to test my ability to engage with these financial sectors as smoothly as possible while also learning; providing the fund with thorough data-first analysis to make informed and important investments to help innovative companies grow.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Aditya Nair';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.26, major = 'Finance, minor in corporate finance', expected_graduation = 'Other', why_hillside = 'I want to join Hillside Ventures because it aligns with my background in finance and my desire to gain hands-on exposure to venture capital and early-stage investing. I graduated with a degree in finance, and while I am currently back at UConn supporting the Volunteer Income Tax Assistance (VITA) program, I am eager to expand my experience beyond tax preparation and into evaluating startups, analyzing business models, and understanding investment strategy. Hillside Ventures would allow me to apply my financial analysis skills in a real-world investment setting while learning how capital is deployed to help innovative companies grow. I am especially interested in gaining exposure to due diligence, market research, and portfolio management, as I continue building a strong foundation for a career in finance and investment management.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by leveraging my finance background and analytical skill set to support thoughtful investment decisions. As a finance graduate from the University of Connecticut, I have experience analyzing financial statements, evaluating risk, and understanding valuation fundamentals. I can assist with due diligence by breaking down business models, assessing revenue projections, and identifying key financial and operational risks. Additionally, my experience working with the Volunteer Income Tax Assistance (VITA) program has strengthened my attention to detail and ability to interpret financial information accurately. I bring a strong work ethic, intellectual curiosity, and willingness to learn: qualities that are essential when evaluating early-stage ventures. I am also comfortable collaborating in team-based environments, contributing to discussions, and presenting insights clearly. Overall, I would contribute disciplined financial analysis, a growth mindset, and a genuine interest in supporting innovative student entrepreneurs.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Rige Grajcevci';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.66, major = 'Psychological Sciences', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jaime-lugo-61692b384', why_hillside = 'As a freshman who wants to get into business, I believe Hillside Ventures can provide me not only with hands-on experience and networking opportunities but also a strong, hardworking community of people with the same interests as me. Through the many positive things I hear from people I know within Hillside, it is a great way to enhance my knowledge and skills in the business world through opportunities that not many other clubs or associations at UConn offer. Through investments made in Hillside Ventures in companies like EnviCore and Natrion, I believe Hillside effectively uses its assets towards companies that are not just profitable but also positively change the world. Hillside would be an overall great opportunity to make a positive impact while also giving real-world experience that is not typically offered at other organizations', contribution = 'As a member, I would be able to contribute assistance and time. I would be able to use my time efficiently to research companies that align with the goals of Hillside. Because sustainability is an important passion of mine, I would look for any startup companies that can make a positive impact on the world and the future. I would also invest a lot of time in assisting others with anything needed. With not many time constraints in my schedule, I would be able to dedicate a lot of my time to Hillside in order to become a reliable and helpful asset to the team.', vertical_interest = 'Sustainability' WHERE name = 'Jaime Lugo';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.38, major = 'Undecided', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/rayden-jones-miller-30a3b9388', why_hillside = 'I am interested in Hillside Ventures because I want early, hands-on exposure to how investment decisions are made in practice. As I plan to apply to UConn''s School of Business, I am actively seeking opportunities that will allow me to grow professionally and apply analytical thinking beyond the classroom. I believe Hillside Ventures provides an environment where I can develop these skills through structured research and real-world evaluation, which is why I have chosen to apply to join the team.

I am particularly drawn to the Consumer Products vertical. Through my experience in retail, I have observed how pricing, placement, branding, and seasonal trends influence purchasing behavior. This experience has strengthened my overall understanding of consumer demand and sparked my interest in analyzing it in a broader, more business-finance context.

Overall, Hillside Ventures represents an opportunity to challenge myself intellectually, collaborate with other driven peers, and contribute meaningfully while building the skills necessary for a future career in business.', contribution = 'Given my experience in the retail industry, I can contribute a practical perspective on consumer behavior and product performance to the Genesis Fund. Working in a fast-paced retail environment has required attention to detail, consistency, and an awareness of demand patterns and purchasing trends to ensure that high-demand products are properly stocked and positioned in the establishment.

In addition, I bring reliability and a structured approach to problem-solving. Balancing academic responsibilities with work has strengthened my time management and accountability skills. When analyzing a situation, I focus on asking thoughtful questions and supporting conclusions with evidence rather than assumptions.

All in all, I am prepared to contribute meaningful research, disciplined analysis, and a grounded perspective to support Hillside''s Genesis Fund.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Rayden Jones-Miller';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.65, major = 'Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jeffreyortizz/', why_hillside = 'I’m interested in Hillside Ventures because it represents the type of environment I genuinely want to be part of. I value being surrounded by driven, like-minded individuals who are curious, motivated, and willing to put in meaningful effort to produce strong outcomes. I’ve always believed that growth and better results come from consistent engagement, discipline, and learning from others, which is why Hillside’s student-led and analytical structure is especially appealing to me. Beyond the technical and analytical experience, I’m particularly excited about the opportunity to connect with founders and learn more about how they developed their ideas, what motivated them to start their companies, and how they navigate challenges. That direct exposure to entrepreneurial thinking and decision-making is something you simply can’t replicate in a classroom. The combination of hands-on experience, collaborative analysis, and real interactions with founders makes Hillside Ventures a uniquely valuable opportunity that aligns closely with both my interests and my approach to personal and professional development.', contribution = 'I believe I could contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing a structured and analytical way of thinking to evaluating opportunities and discussing ideas. I tend to approach problems by breaking them down logically, questioning assumptions, and focusing on the underlying drivers of a business rather than just surface-level narratives. I value skepticism and careful reasoning, which are important when assessing early-stage ventures where uncertainty and incomplete information are common. I’m comfortable interpreting numbers and using them to support broader conclusions, but I also recognize that investing decisions extend beyond financials and require thoughtful judgment. Additionally, I place strong emphasis on clear communication and collaborative discussion, as I enjoy exchanging perspectives and refining ideas with others. Overall, I would aim to contribute disciplined thinking, analytical curiosity, and a balanced approach to evaluating business opportunities.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Jeffrey Ortiz';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.0, major = 'Major: Real Estate and Urban Economics Minor: Psychological Sciences', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/hannah-patz-650095270?utm_source=share&utm_campaign=share_via&utm_content=profile&utm_medium=ios_app', why_hillside = 'I am drawn to Hillside Ventures because of its disciplined investment thesis and structured yet collaborative process. I really value the way the fund is organized into focused sectors while still encouraging cross-team collaboration and shared diligence. As an analyst at Hillside Real Estate, I have fully immersed myself in the investment process, and I am eager to continue building on that foundation in a more venture-focused environment. Being a part of Hillside Ventures would allow me the opportunity to deepen my analytical skillset.', contribution = 'I would contribute to the Genesis Fund by bringing both analytical rigor and genuine passion to the Sports & Wellness vertical. Through my experience with Hillside Real Estate, I have developed strong research and evaluation skills that would translate to venture. Beyond technical skills, I bring a long standing passion for sports and wellness, which allows me to understand trends beyond the academic perspective. I would be a dedicated and proactive member of the team, adding value wherever possible.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Hannah Patz';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.75, major = 'Finance', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/-christiankim', why_hillside = 'Having the experience working for a small start up company last summer it really opened my eyes into how many successful businesses ideas are out there, but they just don’t have enough funding to create a larger scale company or as much profit as they should. I believe the research and work I would be able to do for Hillside Ventures will help Pre-seed to Series A companies out there to get the funding that they deserve.', contribution = 'I believe I bring both the technical skills needed to source and pitch companies as well as a more personable and professional communicator. I also believe that I can be very creative in finding smaller companies if I am chosen to the sports and wellness vertical, as I played sports in high school and spend a lot of free time focusing on sports news as well as fitness/health related trends. On top of that I live very close to the Washington DC area and I believe I can be a valuable resource to use if current, future, or even former hillside students could use if they are looking to network with anyone in that area.', vertical_interest = 'Sports & Wellness' WHERE name = 'Christian Kim';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 4.0, major = 'Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/seanw-mcgowan', why_hillside = 'I am interested in hillside ventures because it provides students with hands-on experience in venture capital which is something I have always been interested in. Being able to engage in experiences beyond the classroom will help me exert myself and enhance my career. Also, being able to meet like-minded peers and build connections will be very beneficial.', contribution = 'I will have a hard-working attitude and a willingness to want to improve. I will ask questions when I am unsure of anything, and collaborate and communicate strongly with others. I will want to get the most out of this opportunity and make it positive for everyone.', vertical_interest = 'Consumer Products' WHERE name = 'Sean McGowan';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.5, major = 'Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2029', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/aj-umali-a4945a3b2/', why_hillside = 'Hillside Ventures, Genesis fund, presents the convergence of innovation, finance, and real-world application that I want to be a part of. Through my coursework as an accounting major at UConn, I have developed a solid understanding of the financial aspects of businesses; however, I am especially interested in financial technologies  and how early-stage startups are changing the flow of capital, processing of transactions, and use of data for decision-making. The potential of Hillside Ventures as a platform to review early-stage companies, learn about venture investing models, and assess risk from a strategic and financial standpoint is highly attractive to me.

In addition, as an international student participating in Genesis, I will have opportunities to gain experience outside of the classroom. Participation in Genesis will provide me with immersion in the U.S. startup and venture community, establish connections with professional networks I may not otherwise have access to, and help me understand the funding and scaling of innovation in this market. Direct interaction with founders, investors, and peers with diverse backgrounds will create a tremendous opportunity for growth in both my career and my life. Participation in Genesis will also allow me to link my technical accounting education with the future orientation of venture capital and fintech innovation, while providing me with a first-hand look at the U.S. business environment.', contribution = 'I can provide high value to the Genesis Fund through my analytical approach and attention to detail when evaluating potential startups. I have experience reviewing and analyzing financial information and can identify cash flow patterns, assess company sustainability, and review the financial assumptions in pitch decks, all of which are key considerations when making decisions about early-stage ventures. I know how to analyze a company''s unit economics, review burn rates, and evaluate the financial assumptions presented in pitch decks, all of which are critical to venture capital and angel investors.

The experiences I have had, both in high school studying business and finance and in jobs where I was financially responsible, have given me the opportunity to be very intentional in how I think about budgeting, cost structures, and profit margins. As a result, I am confident in my ability to contribute to the financial aspects of organizations, and this confidence will enable me to provide thoughtful, well-informed input to support the Genesis team during due diligence and investment discussions.

As well as being a source of technical financial analysis, I look forward to continuing my education and taking an active role in researching industries and creating investment memoranda. Due to my interest in fintech, I may also be able to provide some insight into emerging fintech trends, including digital payment systems, blockchain infrastructure, embedded finance models, and AI-based financial solutions. Although I am an accounting major, I view Genesis as an opportunity to apply my financial knowledge in a venture capital environment while developing my strategic thinking.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Antonio Juan H. Umali';
UPDATE applicants SET gpa = 3.33, major = 'Accounting', expected_graduation = 'Class of 2028', linkedin_url = 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/kaidalgozy/', why_hillside = 'I’m interested in Hillside Ventures because of its focus on investing in early-stage companies that have strong growth potential and long-term impact. I’m especially drawn to the firm’s emphasis on supporting founders beyond just capital offering strategic guidance and hands-on involvement to help businesses scale effectively.', contribution = 'I can contribute to the Genesis Fund by combining my financial analysis background with a strong interest in financial technology and innovation. As an Accounting student, I’m comfortable analyzing financial statements, evaluating risk, and understanding how businesses generate value. In a FinTech context, I can apply those skills to assess scalability, revenue models, user acquisition strategies, and long-term sustainability of digital platforms.', vertical_interest = 'Financial Technology' WHERE name = 'Kaid Algozy';
